CE> is, is there any advantage to combining the flags into one number?  Does it
CE> make the code faster or smaller, or is this just a matter of style?

It makes the source smaller. Look:

$1000000|$200000|$400|8|4|2|1
$0120040f

the second one is 20 bytes shorter :)

Seriously, that makes no difference in perfomance nor makes any useful
things. I suppose (judging by myself) it's just a force of habit to
use this or that. Personally, I can divide a hex number in the 'powers' of 2
quite fast, so I never bothered to use '|'s :)


