Sami had this to say

> On 15-Nov-98, Dimas Caparros wrote:
> > Hola! 
> > can someone make me a little prog? I have tryied it, but no luck...

>-------8< snip --------->
> 
> >   InitCopList 0,44,112,$10418,8,256,0
> >   BitPlanesBitMap 0,1,%11111111
> >   InitCopList 1,156,112,$10418,8,256,0
>                                     A
>                                     |
> Because you use the same palette you dont need this one
> This will make those blank lines between the parts,becasue copper needs
> time to make the palette change

That may be true, but also there is another hardware limitation of 
the Amiga.  When two CopList`s are displayed at the same time, 
there must be a gap of two scanline`s between the CopList`s. You 
can find this on the CopList programming section in the manual. 
I`m afraid there`s not a lot that can be done about it.

Cya
Steven


