@NODE "Mail_31" "A plea for sanity !!!"
 (envelope-from FlameDuck@usa.net)
 (envelope-from FlameDuck@usa.net)
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@usa.net>
Date: Sat, 21 Nov 1998 21:35:14 +0200
Organization: A97
Subject: A plea for sanity !!!
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello.

I just wish people would stop using copperscreens alltogether and start
using intuition ones instead. AMOS users don't have a choice, we do. Lets=

make sure our Games & Applications run on most AMiGA's, eh ?

I am one of the many people who have gotten a Cheap PC monitor so I can u=
se
higher resolutions, and I'm pretty sure people with graphics cards are
having many of the same frustrations that I am, with people insisting on
using 15Khz screens, I mean come on - It's not the 80's anymore.

Besides, most people today have monster CPU's (compared to a 7Mhz 68K or =
a
14Mhz 020) which by far outperform the blitter-copper alliance. I mean su=
re
you can pull tons of cool display tricks with the copper, but at least 60=
%
of all high-end AMiGA users won't be able to see it anyway, so what's the=

point ?

So would people that HAVEN'T figured out how to build 31Khz+ copperlists,=

PLEASE not use copperscreens ? Thank you. =



Greets,
-- =

