Hi,

>I just wish people would stop using copperscreens alltogether and start
>using intuition ones instead. AMOS users don't have a choice, we do. Lets
>make sure our Games & Applications run on most AMiGA's, eh ?

I for one am trying to do an OS friendly game but it is very difficult,
there
is CpuBlitting, Screentags screenmodes to worry about and OS programming
is a bit tricky when you first start on it!  It is also difficult getting
hold of resource and information that you need.  So please don't be so hard
on people who have to resort to a BLITZ mode game, it is by far the easiest
to do. :)

And we are all Amiga & Blitz users....peace man! ;)

Regards,

Alex Smyth



