Hello Dimas.

On 22-Nov-98, Dimas Caparros wrote:

> in my game, I use Sprites, so I can not use WB... you should know that
you
> have an Amiga capable of such screens modes by default, so you are the
> strange one, not us...

A) I still think you shouldn't use sprites. They are SOOO limited.

B) So, now it's strange that I want to upgrade my AMiGA ? Well, Last year=
 I
spent upto 16 hours/day, using my AMiGA for professional work, and after
one week of listening to that annoying 15Khz whine of my Phillips CM8833 =
I
decided to get a real monitor.

C) Of course you know that the meaning of Default is "When all else fails=
",
the meaning of Great is "Extremly large" and Ultimate means "The definate=

last" (Making Ultimate Soccer Manager II (And simmilar titles) a
contradiction in terms.)

D) Well, lets consider maths for a while. Say you where making a comercia=
l
game. Your target market would be at least 30% of all AMiGA owners. Of
these at least 50% would pirate the game, and 15% of the remaining would
not be able to run it at all, resulting in huge financial loses.


Regards
-- =

