@NODE "Mail_48" "Re: AGA or CyberGFX/P96 Screen"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Nov 1998 14:25:25 -0500
Subject: Re: AGA or CyberGFX/P96 Screen

Hi Paul

On 20-Nov-98, Paul Burkey wrote:

> PWest came up with the best idea but it's also an idea I tried
> myself a while ago with no luck. It's based on the 'Foreign' flag
> in the display info so I had another go at trying to get it
> working. Anyway, I got it working now so I decided to send
> some example code. It seems to be able to tell between all
> the modes I have on my system eg, lots of CyberGFX modes
> and lots of PAL modes.
> 
> Let me know if this fails with any particulr modes. It uses lots
> of OS tags so you have to make amigalibs.res resident. I'd
> also like to know if the implimentation is okay. I'm freeing
> the ASL requester but I have to be sure I've not missed
> anything.

The example works fine here (I have AGA only, it correctly shows any of my
available modes as "Native").  But I have only the "standard" NTSC and PAL
modes here, no "super72" or any of that sort.

I made up a small exec and will pass it on to some friends with P96 and CV
to make sure it works for them.

The only thing missing in the example is there wasn't any provisions if the
user hit "cancel" on the requester (ok will then be 0) - but maybe you just
didn't bother with that for the example.

