@NODE "Mail_55" "Re: AHI Sample Length"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 25 Nov 1998 21:56:39 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Nov 1998 21:54:49 +0000
Subject: Re: AHI Sample Length

Hi Daniel,

> Just a simple question......regarding AHI......are the samples limited to
> 128k? i.e the same as the blitz sound commands??
> I'm playing samples through AHI but the cut out after a certain length,
the
> same length as if they are played with Blitz commands.

I mailed you earlier about AHI/sample length problems and I also
spoke about 128k limits... One thing I didn't remind you as the fact
that the AHIFuncs that you've been using are based around the
regular Blitz sample loading functions as well as stanard Blitz sample
structures. Perhaps blitz sample loading or th sample structure is
limited to 128k while AHI itself has no such limits (check out the
quote at the bottom of this posting)

Perhaps there's a need for a custom LoadSound command which
shouldn't be too hard depending on which range or sample formats
you'd like to support. Then again, maybe the problem is with the
AHIFuncs.bb handling of the sample structure.

As I said today, send me a long (archived!) sample and I'll try and
get it to work for you (including looping and volume control...)

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

"The samples can have any length (including odd)"
-- AHI Autodocs



