@NODE "Mail_58" "Re: Amiga Forever!"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 18 Nov 1998 16:11:58 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Nov 1998 16:35:00 +0000
Subject: Re: Amiga Forever!

Hi Hrafn,

> I've recently subscribed to this list and have just checked my mailbox to
> find 70 new messages! :(
> Please tell me there's a `digest' mode where a whole days worth of
> messages arrive to you in ONE glorious long message! (as with other
> mailing lists).

I don't think there's a didegs mode with the blitz-list. However, you
shouldn't
get much more than 15 massages per day (average less than 10 a day). I
would recomend you add a blitz-list folder to YAM an setup a filter that
moves all blitz messages to it. That makes it much easier to deal with
mailing lists. Oh, I'd also recomend you start using YAM2 rather than
that old version...

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_59" "Amiga Forever!"
From: Hrafn <jhines1@mail.usyd.edu.au>
Date: Thu, 19 Nov 1998 00:31:11 +0500
Subject: Amiga Forever!

Holy Toledo!

I've recently subscribed to this list and have just checked my mailbox to
find 70 new messages! :(
Please tell me there's a `digest' mode where a whole days worth of
messages arrive to you in ONE glorious long message! (as with other
mailing lists).

Anyway, enough of this whinging.. I'm a newbie to the wonderful world of
Blitz and hope to one day be able to understand a single line of code.

Seeya's! :) 

/me sits back and absorbs.

-- 

