@NODE "Mail_68" "Re: Aminet Censored!? - (Maybe) Off Topic!"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Nov 1998 07:07:02 -0500
Subject: Re: Aminet Censored!? - (Maybe) Off Topic!

Hi Rui

On 27-Nov-98, Rui Carvalho wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> The strangest thing is happening to me...
> 
> I've uploaded my new proggy *AFM* *1.01* to Aminet 3 times now...
> 
> One on the 12.11 another on the 17.11 and 22.11 but it seems the guys on
> Aminet don't want to make it available!

Aminet only allows files to be re-uploaded again after 10 days.  Once you
upload the program, you must wait at least 10 days before sending it
again.
> 
> I wonder if it is because i've included the following line on the info:
> 
> "We want a directory on Aminet "
>     Made in Blitz Basic"

We have tried before to get a Blitz/ directory on Aminet.  The problem is
that Aminet requires at least 40 (as I remember it - correct me if I'm
wrong, guys) files for a directory.

Yes, we have more than 40 Blitz files in there already - but the problem is
that unless there are at least 40 (or whatever the minimum is) NON-BLITZ
files to leave behind in the basic/ directory, they won't let us move the
Blitz files to a new directory...
> 
> I'm nearly finishing version 2 (several improvements and inovations) but
i
> fear that when i upload it, they won't make it available!

Wait at least 10 days, then try it again.
> 
Later...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




