@NODE "Mail_75" "appicon problem"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 06 Nov 1998 02:22:09 -0500
Subject: appicon problem

Hi everybody,

Please excuse this non "Amiga Rumours" related posting...  ;)

I have a cli command (scsiUtil) which allows me to eject my zip disk and my CD
disc from the shell.

It also works when called from Blitz using Execute_  or SystemTaglist_

But, I want to use it with an appicon, so when I drag the zip or CD's icon on
it, it will be ejected.  Now it works - sort of...

The appropriate disk does eject, but the disk's icon stays on the WB screen!

If I cause another AppEvent by dragging another icon onto the appicon, or just
clicking on the appicon itself (this shows a "quit" requester) then the icon
will disappear...  Otherwise it stays there forever.

When called from the shell, or from a Blitz program without an AppIcon, the
disk's icon does disappear from the WB when the disk is ejected.

Any ideas?  Is there some command I can call to force the WB to refresh?

Thanks for any help or ideas.

Later...
-- 
