@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_82" "Re: Blitting with the OS"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 19 Nov 1998 04:07:27 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Nov 1998 03:56:05 +0000
Subject: Re: Blitting with the OS

Hi,

> How can I blit a shape with OS functions? Does the shape need to be raw
> data or can it also be iff? 

It depends what you want to blit, where you want to Blit it and what
effect you want. The most simple OS Blit of all is to Blit a shape to
a Window with a basic 'cookie cut' effect. That can be done with the
WBlit command although you could try and look clever by using
BltMaskBitMapRastPort_() although that would be showing off :)

If you want to know more about Blitting with the OS I'd take a look
at the graphics.library functions like BltBitMap, BltBitMapRastPort,
BltClear, BltMaskBitMapRastPort. It all depends on how complex
you need to get.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

