From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 20 Nov 98 19:46:44 +1000
Subject: Blitz Basic Status
Encoding: 7bit

Hi,

This is my first posting to this list.

Could someone please bring me up to date with the current status of
Blitz Basic?  

Is anyone actively supporting the language.  The last I heard was that
Red When Excited were asking for wish lists for the next release...
then nothing.  They don't seem to be answering e-mails any more.

I'v had BUM's up to 10 (I think that was the last one - that's what
they said anyway) and then bought BSS.  Is there anything else that I
should have?  What about the BB 2.1 CD.  Does that contain anything
else useful/essential?

Antything else I should know??

Thanks in advance


Excited
-- 
Tony Rolfe
