@NODE "Mail_87" "Blitz List files"
From: Donovan Reeve <bubby.lnk@ispi.net>
Date: Thu, 26 Nov 1998 10:27:25 +0500
Subject: Blitz List files

On 25-Nov-98, Paul Burkey flashed:

>Really, this is a "give and take" list which means you should
>be available to help others when possible If you're not a member
>then it becomes "take" only. Ahh well, the mailing list is available
>for read-only on aminet each month, LOL :)

  Believe it or not, I save ALL messages to the Blitz List in a
permenant archive.  I do this so I can study them at my leisure and
learn from them. I am hoping to find time this winter to boil some of
it down into helpful instructions which I will make available to all.

  By saving them myself I get the whole list, even if some don't make
it to aminet as happened last June.  If I miss any then I can get those
from Aminet.

  Storage isn't a problem as I have over 11 Gigabytes of hard drive
space and a CD-rom writer, as well as Zip and Bournelli drives.  :)

  If anybody misses anything they just HAVE to have, let me know and
I will send you the missing messages as long as the requested amount
isn't rediculous.  Preferably ask for them by topic or author.


cacha later,

Donovan Reeve (bubby.lnk@ispi.net)




