@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_89" "Re: Blitz on PC?"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 6 Nov 1998 23:01:07 +0000
From: "Nick Chapman" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: Re: Blitz on PC?
Date: Fri, 6 Nov 1998 22:38:19 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

No, I'm afraid that's not being done. The programmers of Blitz Basic are now
working on sequels to Roadkill and Guardian (unfortunately on the PC) and a
Playstation emulator for the PC. They have no plans to port Blitz to the PC
currently. I know it would be nice to programme stuff for the Amiga then
port it easily to the PC to sell to a wider user base, but that isn't
possible without using C. Blitz is unique and Amiga-specific.

Nick / Skillo

