Organization: University of London (QMW)
Date: Tue, 17 Nov 1998 11:39:34 +0000
encoding: 7BIT
Subject: Borders round text


Hello all,
	This has been bugging me for quite a while.  When you 
install newicons, you get an option if you want an outline around 
text or a text shadow. I know you to do a drop shadow of text (i.e 
print the text a pixel to the left aswell) but how does the outline 
work? Is it a function of AmigaDos, or as I suspect, a patch on 
NewIcons behalf? If it is a patch, could some-one give me an 
example of how to do it quickly?

Thanks
Steven



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_92" "Re: Borders round text"
Date: Tue, 17 Nov 1998 15:19:14 +0300
From: Andrew "Notorious" Boyarintsev <bandrew@miem.edu.ru>
Organization: Looker House
Subject: Re: Borders round text
Encoding: 7bit

Hello S.J.CROY,

Tuesday, November 17, 1998, you wrote:

SJC> NewIcons behalf? If it is a patch, could some-one give me an
SJC> example of how to do it quickly?

Print your text one pixel right of the actual position,
then one pixel left, then one up, then one down. And then print the
text on the position, but with the background color :)

 %%%  %%%  %%%  %*%  %*%  %*%
 %*%  %**  ***  ***  ***  *%*
 %%%  %%%  %%%  %%%  %*%  %*%



WBR, Andrew "Notorious" Boyarintsev

member Team *AMIGA*                      http://come.to/lkr

... UI125:-/CMHFAJEFDCVADGMDLfCDGDGFPIHfBBHILRDFRAMOIIABCOJ

...I said I loved you but I lied... (C) M.Bolton




