@NODE "Mail_97" "Re: Bug in EFMUILib"
          Paris Wed, 11 Nov 1998 12:21:21 +0100 (MET)
          Paris Wed, 11 Nov 1998 12:21:19 +0100 (MET)
Date: Wed, 11 Nov 1998 12:11:28 +0100
From: Erwan Fouret <Erwan.Fouret@wanadoo.fr>
Subject: Re: Bug in EFMUILib

--=====================_910779088==_

Hello!

  Andreas Falkenhahn wrote:

>The problem that I complained yesterday on the list is caused by EFMUI Lib.
>
>If you open more than 14 mui window objects your application will crash
>sooner
>or later. 
>
>I attach some source to this mail. You can run it as many times as you like
>it. It won`t
>crash. But if you then uncomment the two lines which open the 15th window,
>it`ll
>crash after two or three compiles. It would be very kind of you if anyone
>could test
>this -- because the problem is still a strange one and I want to know if
>it`s only on
>my amiga.

  Well, you're right, that is (or even was now) a bad "bug" (well, in fact
it's more a limitation than a bug). Actually, the maximum nulber of tags
in te application taglist was fixed to 20 and couldn't be changed. So, with
15 windows a the 6 application attributes commands (title, etc) you go over
it! Well, I send here now a fixed version. Now, you can set the number of
tags you want for the application with MUISetMaximumTags like with other
object.
By default the max number is set to 51 so your example works now fine :)

  Bye!

--=====================_910779088==_
Encoding: base64
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="EFMUILibFixed.lzx"

