@NODE "Mail_100" "Re: Busy Pointers!!!"
          Paris Thu, 5 Nov 1998 22:33:42 +0100 (MET)
          Paris Thu, 5 Nov 1998 22:33:40 +0100 (MET)
From: Gigandet Jean-Marc <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
        Blitz-List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Thu, 05 Nov 1998 22:33:33 +0100
Subject: Re: Busy Pointers!!!
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello, I've already give this routines to other blitz users. Here it is o=
nce more :

This is to show the busy pointer. I don't know if you can use it before 3=
=2E0.
I use these routines :

BusyPointer:
;This sets the busypointer for the window
  tags\a=3D#WA_BusyPointer
  tags\b=3DTrue
  tags\c=3D#WA_PointerDelay
  tags\d=3DTrue
  tags\e=3D#TAG_END
  SetWindowPointerA_ Peek.l(Addr Window(#NumWdw0)),tags
Return

StandardPointer:
; This set the standard pointer for the window
  ClearPointer_(Peek.l(Addr Window(#NumWdw0)))
Return

Regards
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
A1200 030/28 + 68881 + 8 Mo + Quantum 635 Mo + Wd 60 Mo
             + M1438S + Deskjet 690C + UsR 33600.
