@NODE "Mail_103" "Re: Busy Pointers!!!"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Fri, 06 Nov 1998 21:55:14 -0500
Subject: Re: Busy Pointers!!!
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 05-Nov-98, S9225796 wrote:


>> Does anyone here no how to change the mouse cursor
>> into an intuition busy pointer in amiga mode?
>> =

>> If so, please could you let me know as this would be
>> a great help for some of the programs I am working on!

Hi,

you could you the RTLockWindow and RTUnlockWindow commands. The problem i=
s
that they use the reqtools.library and maybe you don't want this. So I co=
ded
two functions (LockWindow{} and UnlockWindow{}) which do the same (also t=
he
syntax is the same). LockWindow{} not only displays a busy pointer, but b=
locks
the input for the given window too. Well, the busy pointer is displayed o=
nly
on a 3.0 OS, but the input is blocked even on a 2.0 OS. Here they are:

  Function.l LockWindow{Win.l}              ; Window#
    Lock.l=3DAllocMem_(SizeOf .Requester,1)
    If Lock
      Win=3DPeek.l(Addr Window(Win))
      InitRequester_(Lock)
      If Request_(Lock,Win)
        *Exec.Library=3DPeek.l(4)
        If *Exec\lib_Version=3D>39
          Dim tag.TagItem(1)
          tag(0)\ti_Tag=3D#WA_BusyPointer,-1
          tag(1)\ti_Tag=3D#TAG_END
          SetWindowPointerA_ Win,&tag(0)
        EndIf
      Else
        FreeMem_ Lock,SizeOf .Requester
        Lock=3D0
      EndIf
    EndIf
    Function Return Lock
  End Function

  Statement UnlockWindow{Win.l,Lock.l}      ; Window#,Lock
    Win=3DPeek.l(Addr Window(Win))
    *Exec.Library=3DPeek.l(4)
    If *Exec\lib_Version=3D>39
      Delay_ 5
      Dim tag.TagItem(0)
      tag(0)\ti_Tag=3D#TAG_END
      SetWindowPointerA_ Win,&tag(0)
    EndIf
    EndRequest_ Lock,Win
    FreeMem_ Lock,SizeOf .Requester
  End Statement

You can use them like that:

  Lock.l=3DLockWindow{0}
    ...
    ;do the job in any case
    ...
  If Lock Then UnlockWindow{0,Lock}

or like that:

  Lock.l=3DLockWindow{0}
  If Lock
    ...
    ;do the job just if LockWindow worked
    ...
    UnlockWindow{0,Lock}
  EndIf

I hope they can be useful for many of you.

C ya...




-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

   _____________________________________
