Hello Dimas.

On 20-Nov-98, Dimas Caparros wrote:

> I have a 256 bitmap, and I am using sprites x4 and x16 colors

> x4 colors sprites are at top of the screen for score, and x16 are on th=
e
> rest of the screen.

> Currently I am using diferent channels.

> 1-is this possible? (I can not see it work corectly because the color
> problem avobe and maybe it is not possible to mix 2 of 4 colors and 2 o=
f
16
> colors)

Yes, and no. A 16 pixel wide 4 colour sprite uses one sprite channel, and=
 a
16 pixe;l, 16 colour sprite uses two (or is it four). Anyway, all of thes=
e
things must be taken into considererations when assigning sprite channel
numbers. Is there any particulary reason you use sprites instead of, lets=

say BOB's (or shapes, as they are called in Blitz teriminology.)

> 2-How to reutilise the same sprite channel on the rest of the screen
> (currently I am using different channels, and they will never overlap)

Erm, in ASM yes, it is. In Blitz however I suspect you could do so by usi=
ng
two different coplists, but I havn't done any "hard codeing" in Blitz, fo=
r
that purpose, I'm much too fond of ASM...

> 3-How to change the colors of the sprites, using a different set for to=
p
10
> pixels and another set for the rest? (you see, just a 16 colors change)=


You can't. Or rather you can, but it's not worth the effort. Even in ASM =
it
would take HUGE dynamic alterations to the copperlist, and since this is
next to impossible to do in blitz, I would find another sollution. Looks
like Shapes are the only way out for you amigo. (Remember sprites are
limited to the colours in palette entries 16+ (or rather 17+ as colour 16=

is transparent) BOB's on the otherhand can utilise the entire palette.)

Of course, I could be entirely wrong. But it's not likely. :o)


Regards
-- =

