@NODE "Mail_111" "Re: Change sprite colors"
From: Sami =?iso-8859-1?Q?N=E4=E4t=E4nen?= <sami.naatanen@dlc.fi>
Date: Fri, 20 Nov 1998 18:29:22 +0200
Organization: Diverse
Subject: Re: Change sprite colors
Encoding: quoted-printable


> > 3-How to change the colors of the sprites, using a different set for =
top
> 10
> > pixels and another set for the rest? (you see, just a 16 colors chang=
e)

> You can't. Or rather you can, but it's not worth the effort. Even in AS=
M it
> would take HUGE dynamic alterations to the copperlist, and since this i=
s
> next to impossible to do in blitz, I would find another sollution. Look=
s
> like Shapes are the only way out for you amigo. (Remember sprites are
> limited to the colours in palette entries 16+ (or rather 17+ as colour =
16
> is transparent) BOB's on the otherhand can utilise the entire palette.)=


> Of course, I could be entirely wrong. But it's not likely. :o)

Well partly you are :) in AGA amigas there is a tiny NIBLE which controls=

the position where the Sprite palette offset starts (0-14)
the first color register is counted using the next formula: (n+1)*16
or was it n*16 :) I can't remember now, but it worked I tested it about
year ago. :) You can found those bits from the help of initcoplist comman=
d.
There are also a special XOR bitfield which can modify
the dualplayfield color by XORing the bitfield with the contents of
bitplane data!!!

More info... can't be found anywhere because they (commodeore etc) never
published those new AGA registers. :( So you just have to try. :)

