> it should not be a hard thing... is there a way to change the color 0 a=
t
> the middle of the screen? It have to be, as the commands CustomColors,
> DisplayRGB and/or DisplayRainbow seems to be set for this purpose... if=

you
> can change background color, you can change any color... the problem is=

> that the manual in this issue is not writen, so I need a little help
> here...

Okay, so what is the propblem then, just use DisplayRGB...

The syntax is DisplayRGB Coplist#,register,line,r,g,b

Coplist#    Is the number of the copperlist which you are yuseing to crea=
te
your non-systemfriendly display.
register    Which colour register. 0-255 in this case.
line            Which screen offset, or how far diown the screen you want=
change the colour. (Remember that a display should start at line 42)
r,g,b        Are the RGB values for the colour you want to change.

Now, remember that you have to put a -4 value in your initcoplist (Or
something). And the correct way to do it is still useing blocks and maps.=

Preferably on a system screen....

> I used to be an AMOS guy (and not a bad one) and really it is going har=
d
