@NODE "Mail_115" "Re: Correct use of CludgeBitmap + Free Bitmap"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 22 Nov 1998 02:52:17 +0000
From: "Dave" <dave@nbsamiga.demon.co.uk>
Subject: Re: Correct use of CludgeBitmap + Free Bitmap
Date: Sun, 22 Nov 1998 02:52:22 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit


-----Original Message-----
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: 22 November 1998 01:03
Subject: Correct use of CludgeBitmap + Free Bitmap


>Hi,
>
>I reserve some memory then use CludgeBitmap to force the new
>bitmap to use my reserved memory. Then later in the code I
>need to free both the bitmap and the memory. What order should
>this be done in? I guess, 'free bitmap' then 'freemem'..
>
>Does this explain the point behind the bitmaps _isreal element?


_isreal simply tells blitz that it didn`t allocate the memory for the bitmap
itself (mainly for screensbitmap) when it frees the bitmap (or when end is
reached). I`m actually not sure whether cludgebitmap sets this flag...if i
does it probably means I`ve probably forgot to free the memory after the
bitmap (expecting blitz to free it for me)....whooops..

Dave

P.s. Can you please not ask questions which means I have to spend hours
going through all my old code to check it`s correct :)




