--BOUNDARY.7612.172.271016288.1
Encoding: quoted-printable

Le 03-Nov-98, Martin Au=DFem a =E9crit:

>Hi,

>how is it possible zu add x days to a date in Blitz2?

Hi Martin,

this is the source I converted. I use a newtype to store the date :
   Newtype .Date
      day.b
      month.b
      year.w
   EndNewtype

You need this because a function can't return 3 values. You could also wr=
ite 3
functions : one for update the day, another for the month, and again for =
the
year.
In my example, the actual date is replaced by the future date (actual + d=
ays
to add).

In fact, I use 3 functions :
- 1 to find if the year contains 365 or 366 days
- 1 to find the number of days in a month (february changes, so we need t=
he
previous function)
- 1 to change the date

I wish this is what you need,

Regards,

                                 Mathias

-- =

Recherche stage de DESS pour d=E9but juin.
Sujet : d=E9veloppement d'une application informatique dans la chimie et/=
ou
l'environnement

Amigafans, visitez le site http://www.quartz.fr/amigapower/

--BOUNDARY.7612.172.271016288.1

; Date2.bb2 - To find the new date after addition of a number of days
; 04/11/98
; Mathias Parnaudeau

WBStartup
NoCli
FindScreen 0

; I suppose you have a date in a structure like that :

NEWTYPE .Date                           ; Useful for DaysIn function
  day.b
  month.b
  year.w
End NEWTYPE

DEFTYPE .Date Today

; Does a year contains 365 (0 returned) or 366 days (1 returned) ?
Function.b Bissextile{y.w}
  DEFTYPE .b res                        ; for result
  If (y MOD 4 <> 0)
    res=0
  Else
    If (y MOD 100 <> 0) res=1
      res=1
    Else
      If (y MOD 400 = 0) OR (y=1900)
        res=1
      Else
        res=0
      EndIf
    EndIf
  ;EndIf

  Function Return res
End Function

; return the number of days in the month m of the year y
Function.b NbDaysThisMonth{m.w,y.w}
  DEFTYPE .b NbDays
  If m=2
    If Bissextile{y.w}=1
      NbDays=29;
    Else
      NbDays=28;
    EndIf
  Else
    If (m.w=4) OR (m.w=6) OR (m.w=9) OR (m.w=11)
      NbDays=30
    Else
      NbDays=31
    EndIf
  EndIf
  Function Return NbDays
End Function

; change the values in the variable Today.Date
Statement DaysIn{Amount.w}
  SHARED Today.Date
  DEFTYPE .b MonthSize

  While (Amount>0)
    MonthSize=NbDaysThisMonth{Today\month,Today\year}

    If (Amount+Today\day)>MonthSize
      Amount=Amount-(MonthSize-Today\day)
      Today\month+1
      Today\day=0
      If Today\month=13
        Today\month=1
        Today\year+1
      EndIf
    Else
      Today\day+Amount;
      Amount=0;
    EndIf
  Wend
End Statement

;------------------

; Main program, just to check if it works :-)

Window 0,20,50,350,100,$0,"Date",1,2

; Values chosen for the example

Today\day=4
Today\month=11
Today\year=1998

DaysToAdd.w=252

If Bissextile{Today\year}
  NPrint Str$(Today\year)+" contains 366 days"
Else
  NPrint Str$(Today\year)+" contains 365 days"
EndIf
NPrint ""

DaysIn{DaysToAdd.w}
NPrint "In "+Str$(DaysToAdd.w)+" days, the date will be : "
NPrint ""
NPrint Str$(Today\day)+"/"+Str$(Today\month)+"/"+Str$(Today\year)

MouseWait

Free Window 0

End


--BOUNDARY.7612.172.271016288.1--




@ENDNODE
