On 19 Nov 98 23:18:13 -0100 Martin Außem said:
> Hi,
> 
> has anyone written a function that returns the name of a day
> after entering the date?
> 
> For example: What day is 1999,February 21st? (Sunday, Monday etc.)
> 
> I have an old function that appeared in an AMIGA-magazine some
> years ago, but there is still a bug in.
> 
> Can anyone help me?
> 
The attached function gives the day name, given a day number.

The day number is given by the WeekDay function which is valid after
the Date$ function.  So use Temp$ = Date$(Numdays("25/12/1993"))
folowed by DayName$ = DayofWeek{WeekDay}

PS  This is my first reply to this list.  Does the Reply To function
not work??  Do we have to retype the list address every time???

Cheers

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

--=_=8<==MD23655CA5D-49B4578C==8<=_=
Encoding: plain (7/8 bit)
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="DayofWeek.fun"
X-MD2-FilePath: Ram:DayofWeek.fun

Function.s DayofWeek{day.b}

a$=Mid$("Sunday   Monday   Tuesday  WednesdayThursday Friday   Saturday ",day*9+1,9)

Function Return StripTrail$(a$,32)

End Function

--=_=8<==MD23655CA5D-49B4578C==8<=_=--
(end of MIME multipart message)


