Subject: Re: DefLibs

Hi Centro,

On 19-Nov-98, Centro Amiga wrote:

> BTW: Thanks for GuiGFX, but the example doesn`t work.
>          Maybe it`s because you got a If (Window .........)
>          Well, Window doesn`t give back a return value.
>          NWindow does, but you need a taglist.

Odd, Window will return back a value on my version of Blitz.  Maybe you
have
an old AcidLibs file or window library?

Anyway, you can do this instead of the "If Window... blah blah..."

"Window Blah blah..."         ; the regular way
If peek.l (addr Window(0))    ; or whatever window number

This will tell you if the window is open.
> 
> Oh, almost forgot about this. Can you people try the guigfx examples
> and give out a report? In my CSPPC/CVPPC the plasma example
> gives between 36 to 71 fps. How about in your systems? We need to
> know how fast it will go if we`re gonna use it

Well, on my AGA 030 x 50 (NTSC), it goes about 140 - 150 frames per minute.
And it's a rather small window it runs in, too.

I think (for AGA anyway) it's use would be more for colour remapping for
applications, and graphic manipulation/editing than for animations or
games. 


