Over the past few millennia numerous people wrote:

>DefLibs, Libnums, Tokens blah blah...

Just to add my two-pennyworth, I fit new userlibs in between older ones,
using numbers below 200, with no problems whatsoever (and Acid has never
complained about it...  (;   )On the subject of Libnums, I usually have to
change any new lib number so it doesn't clash with existing libs.  This is
easily done by using a hex editor and editing the 38th byte of the .obj file
to whatever number, and then recompiling DefLibs (or not Mikkel (;  )
although I'm sure you all knew that.  Also, on the subject of tokenizing,
no-one will ever have any tokenizing problems if we all distribute source
code as ascii.  Just an idea.

Regards

Scott

xyz.scott@virgin.net




