@NODE "Mail_153" "Re: deleting a shape or getting coords for a shape"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 16 Nov 1998 20:20:32 +0000
From: "Nick Chapman" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: Re: deleting a shape or getting coords for a shape
Date: Mon, 16 Nov 1998 20:04:44 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

A shape is simply an instruction for the blitter to copy one area of memory
into another: in this case a graphic onto the screen. You decide the
co-ordinates when using the Blit, Block (etc.) commands. They then become a
permanent part of the screen, although Queues and Buffers can be used to
replace the background. You need to store the co-ordinates of your blitting
in a variable.

eg.:

Dim _alienx(4),_alieny(4)

For x=0 to 4
    _alienx(x)=Rnd(320)
    _alieny(x)=Rnd(256)
    ;then the blitting or whatever
Next

The _alienx and _alieny arrays will hold your co-ordinates. As for deleting
shapes, try "Free Shape" if you mean getting the shape out of memory, or
using Buffers or Queues if you mean removing the shape from screen. Read the
manual (ha-ha) for an explanation of queues and buffers.

Nick

