@NODE "Mail_162" "Re: File Seek"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sat, 14 Nov 1998 22:51:27 -0500
Subject: Re: File Seek

Hi Mathias

On 13-Nov-98, Mathias PARNAUDEAU wrote:
> Hi all,
> 
> I need to use Seek_ instead of Fileseek, but I don't exactly understand
the
> difference between Position and Offset in :
> 
> res.l=Seek_(file,position,offset)
> 
> I suppose someone know ... :-)

Well, the answer is that the Blitz "help key" info is incorrect.

The command really is:

res.l=Seek_(file, position, mode)

file is a pointer to the filehandle  -  you can use the Open_ command to get
this.

position is how many bytes you want to move from the current position.  This
can be either + or -  or 0 to find out your current position in the file. 

mode can be either #OFFSET_BEGINNING, #OFFSET_CURRENT, or #OFFSET_END


Let's say your filehandle is stored as *fh

To skip ahead 20 bytes from the current position:

res.l=Seek_(*fh,20,#OFFSET_CURRENT)


To read the last 30 bytes of the file:

res.l=Seek_(*fh,-30,#OFFSET_END)


res will return the current position in the file  or -1 if there is an
error.
 

Later...
-- 
