Without going into the depths of enforcing rules I'd like to comment that
when using structured programming techniques this problem can never
happen. Of course there are often times when bad structure is 'okay',
especially when it's to gain extra speed for games or a similar excuse.
So, maybe you can think about your problem a little more and work
out the proper way to do it in a structured fasion or maybe you can
work out a cludge to make it work.

