@NODE "Mail_179" "Re: God damn list views!!!"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Nov 1998 07:17:33 -0500
Subject: Re: God damn list views!!!

Hi Matt

On 30-Nov-98, S9225796 wrote:

> My problem is that I need to know the tag so that when an item is
> selected, it remains highlighted. Does anyone kno the tag, or how to do
> it?

Needs Amigalibs.res:

  GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,0
  GTListView  blah, blah,blah.....

And yes, "0" is correct.  I know it seems like this would make it not show,
but try it! This will make it show the current selected item as highlited.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_180" "Re: God damn list views!!!"
Date: Mon, 30 Nov 1998 05:05:43 -0800 (PST)
From: Thomas Cobb <thomcobb@yahoo.com>
Subject: Re: God damn list views!!!


---S9225796 <S9225796@Rothervalley.ac.uk> wrote:
 
> My problem is that I need to know the tag so that when an item is
> selected, it remains highlighted. Does anyone kno the tag, or how to
do
> it?

I think the tag you need to set true is #GTLV_ShowSelected.  Add this
line just before you define the listview:

...
GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected,True
GTListview ....
...

	Thom

