@NODE "Mail_181" "Re: God damn list views!!!"
          Paris Mon, 30 Nov 1998 23:15:14 +0100 (MET)
From: Gigandet Jean-Marc <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Mon, 30 Nov 1998 22:50:26 +0100
Subject: Re: God damn list views!!!
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello

> My problem is that I need to know the tag so that when an item is
> selected, it remains highlighted. Does anyone kno the tag, or how to do=

> it?

you should try something like this :
        - if your ListView doesn't have a string gadget attached to it :
                  GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected, 0                           =
     ; 0 means NULL (see autodocs)
                  GTListView  NumGadList, NumGadget, ...

        - if your ListView does have a string gadget attached to it :
                  GTString     NumGadList, NumStringGadget, ...
                  *StrGad.Gadget =3D GtGadPtr(NumGadList, NumStringGadget=
)
                  GTTags #GTLV_ShowSelected, *StrGad                    ;=
 Pointer to the string gadget structure
                  GTListView  NumGadList, NumListGadget, ...


Regards
