Subject: GTListViews (will they never go away)

Hi everybody,

 I was wondering what everyone thought about the best way to have 
multiple items from a listview selected, without having to use OS3+ 
for the callback hook?

 It needs to be able to work with any font, so it would probably look 
quite tacky if I done:
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D                  =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
|  Item 1   |                  |* Item 1   |
|  Item 2   |   Select Item 1  |  Item 2   |
|  Item 3   |                  |  Item 3   |
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D                  =3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D

 As proportional fonts would have them all misaligned. It would look 
not as bad if the marks were at the end of the string, but it would 
still look poor.

 Alternativey, is there any way that you can get intuition messages 
as the listview is being scrolled, then I could have another area for 
drawing the marks, which would allow both to be justified properly.

 Or would the best thing to be just having another listview with all 
the selected items in it (which I don't really want to use).

 This is bugging me as I don't want to go to OS3 just for one damned 
thing!!

chao


