@NODE "Mail_189" "Re: GTMX Gadgets"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 15:35:12 -0500
Subject: Re: GTMX Gadgets

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1747987344.1

Hi S.J.CROY

On 23-Nov-98, S.J.CROY wrote:
> 
> Hello
>     Just a small question.  Can anyone give some example 
> code for reading (and setting) the values of GTMX gadgets?  Do 
> you have to use GTTags or something?

I hope this little example is what you are looking for.
>
 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1747987344.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="gtmx.asc"

WBStartup
WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0
Window 0,20,20,200,100,$1000|$8,"MX test",1,0

;OK, now we need a GT gadgetlist

face.w=2   ;let's show item 3 as selected to start with

GTMX 0,0,80,20,200,70,"",$80,"Item 1|Item 2|Item 3|Item 4|Item 5",face

AttachGTList 0,0

Repeat

  ev.l=WaitEvent

  Select ev

    Case $20            ;GTMX returns $20, NOT $40!
      face.w=EventCode  ;tells which face is selected
      item.w=face+1
      WLocate 0,0
      NPrint "Item "+Str$(item)+" is selected"

    Case $200 ;the close gadget!
      DetachGTList 0
      Free Window 0
      End
  End Select

Forever

--BOUNDARY.1747987344.1--




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_190" "GTMX Gadgets"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    24 Nov 98 09:37:46 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 24 Nov 1998 09:36:30 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: GTMX Gadgets

 Here's a little source to set them after they have been created. I 
think that this doesn't work if you make the MX gagdet have an ID 
before the Buttons (obviously changing all the references to the 
gadget IDs and what value to set the MX to).

 Oh yes, amigalibs.res...

WBStartup
DEFTYPE.w

WbToScreen 0
WBenchToFront_

GTButton 0,0,120,20,100,14,"Set to Good",$10
GTButton 0,1,120,40,100,14,"Set to Bad",$10
GTButton 0,2,120,60,100,14,"Set to Ugly",$10
GTMX 0,3,120,80,20,20,"",2,"Good|Bad|Ugly"

Window 0,0,0,640,200,$100f,"Adfds",-1,-1

AttachGTList 0,0

While ev.l<>#IDCMP_CLOSEWINDOW
  ev =3D WaitEvent
  Select ev
    Case #IDCMP_GADGETUP
      g.w =3D GadgetHit
      If g>=3D0 AND g<=3D2 Then GTSetAttrs 0,3,#GTMX_Active,g
  End Select
Wend

DetachGTList 0
Free GTList 0

CloseWindow 0
CloseScreen 0
End


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694


@ENDNODE
