--BOUNDARY.3439304.3
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello S.J.CROY
Still getting problems with GTMX gadgets. Well perhaps you are using an o=
ld Blitz version ... mine is 2.1 with BSS.
May be your code is wrong. I've attached a small example to test your com=
piler.

Regards
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
A1200 030/28 + 68881 + 8 Mo + Quantum 635 Mo + Wd 60 Mo
             + M1438S + Deskjet 690C + UsR 33600.
HURRICANE, TURRICAN, well, that's a good mix.
Both should visit Redmond ...

--BOUNDARY.3439304.3
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="GTMX.asc"

#tag=$80080000
#GTMX_Active=#tag+10          ; Active one in mx gadget
#GTBB_Recessed=#tag+51        ; BevelBox Recessed

#GTBut = 50
#GtMXG = 51

FindScreen 0                                            ; Get Screen 0 (WB)


GTButton 2,#GTBut, 10,10,80,15,"GT_BUTTON",0            ; Create button gadget

GTMX     2,#GtMXG,200,10,80,15,"GTMX",$1,"1st|2nd|3rd"  ; Create GTMX gadget


Window 0,20,0,420,100,$1000|$F,"HELLO",1,2,2            ; Create window


AttachGTList 2,0                        ; Attach GtList to the window

GTSetAttrs 2,#GtMXG,#GTMX_Active,0      ; Active one is first in GTMX



Repeat                                  ; Loop until window is closed
  ev.l=WaitEvent                        ; wait for next event
  If ev = 64 AND GadgetHit = #GTBut     ; if gadget hit and it's the button
    I.l = I + 1                         ;
    J.b = I MOD 3                       ; J = remainder of I / 3
    GTSetAttrs 2,#GtMXG,#GTMX_Active,J  ; set the GTMX gadget
  EndIf
Until ev=$200                           ; until click on the close gadget

End

--BOUNDARY.3439304.3--




@ENDNODE
