@NODE "Mail_196" "Re: GTShape"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 03 Nov 1998 16:20:27 -0500
Subject: Re: GTShape

Hi Mathias,

On 03-Nov-98, Mathias PARNAUDEAU wrote:
> Hi Blitzers,
> 
> I have a window with GT gadgets on, and I tried to add a shape too. I use :
> 
> GTShape #GTList,#MyShape,x,y,$10,0
> 
> ans I also have :
> 
>   - before : DecodeShapes 0,?shapedata
> 
>   - and after (at the end) :   shapedata:
>                                             IncBin "myshape.iff"
>                                             even
> 
> And nothing appears :-(
> Other gadgets defined work fine.

DecodeShapes works only on Blitz shape files.  It will not work with a
standard iff pic or brush.  You must save your shape(s) as a Blitz shapes file
before you IncBin it.

You can use one of the shape making utilities to create the shapes file, or
write your own small program to do this.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




