Date: Tue, 03 Nov 1998 23:30:00 +0100
Subject: Re: GTShape
Encoding: quoted-printable

The answer to your problem is you're trying to use DecodeShapes with an I=
FF file ! =

DecodeShapes needs a Shape file. You can use RedShapeZ (and then reboot i=
f you don't get a software failure ...) to create it, or if you still wan=
t to use an IFF file, try DecodeILBM, or LoadShape.
Regards, ...
