Hey, man.

We've been through this before. You can't INCbin an IFF file and expect it
to work as a shape. You can only INCbin a shape for this purpose. The best
way of all is to use the RedShapeZ that comes with the BSS to save out a
shape file, and use the commands in the RIShapes Library to include them in
your code. This way, they can even be compressed with Stonecracker.

Nick / Skillo

