Hi !!

I noticed some people here talking about guigfx. Well, that piece of
software really rocks. I just wrote a little example program for guigfx.
It`s attached to this mail aswell as the guigfx.res which is needed
for running it.

Since I did not wrote a complete bb2 library for it, you need to convert
the
guigfx fd include with fdconvert and remake your deflibs. Then copy the
attached
guigfx.res to your local blitzlibs: and then you can compile the example. 

The example lets you choose a picture (datatypes supported) and displays it
in a window on workbench with automatically remapping it to the wb`s
palette. Scaling through resizing the window is supported. 

Let me know if it works for you (especially on cybergraphx or picasso96)

Have fun with it
 
-- 
Greetings,

           Andreas

email: Andreas.Falkenhahn@gmx.de             Software Failure of Airsoft
Softwair, Coder   
WWW: http://www.airsoft.home.pages.de      A1200/040T, 40mhz, 2.0GB HD,
18MB
Ram, 33.600 Modem          

