it
> in a window on workbench with automatically remapping it to the wb`s
> palette. Scaling through resizing the window is supported. 
> 
> Let me know if it works for you (especially on cybergraphx or picasso96)

Well, I have only an AGA system, but the program works very well here.  And
fast too!  Nice work.

The only problem I had was that the ILBMinfo command won't work on anything
other than ILBM pictures - on others (.jpeg, .gif, etc) it opens only a
tiny window.

I cludged the example to always open at least 100 x 100 window... then it
will load .jpeg, gif, and other formats.

There is a command in GUIGFX.library to get the pictures attributes (width,
height, and so on), but I can not understand how to work it.  It returns
the number of attributes it is able to get, but where does the actual
information go?

Do you have any ideas how to make this work?  

Thanks.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




