@NODE "Mail_208" "Re: GuiGfx for BB2"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Nov 1998 19:19:50 -0500
Subject: Re: GuiGfx for BB2

Hi Andreas,

On 18-Nov-98, Andreas Falkenhahn wrote:
> Am 16-Nov-98 schrieb Curt Esser:
> 
>> Hi Andreas,

>> 
>> Well, I have only an AGA system, but the program works very well here. 

>> The only problem I had was that the ILBMinfo command won't work on
> anything
>> other than ILBM pictures - on others (.jpeg, .gif, etc) it opens only a
>> tiny window.
> oops, yeah, IlbmInfo of course only works with ilbm pics

> The GetPictureAttrs() command is really strange, it actually returns zero
> everytime I try it.........don`t know how that one works
>> 
>> Do you have any ideas how to make this work?  
> no, but I`ve done it in an other way. I`m loading the picture in with
> NewDTObj()
> from datatypes.library and then obtain the width and height via intuition
> GetAttrs().
> That actually works fine. I attach you the updated demo and guigfx.res
> (also
> updated
> with some datatypes tags)
>

Yes, it works perfect!  And the rescaling is done so fast, too!  This will
be very useful, I think.

Nice work, thanks again.



                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




