@NODE "Mail_211" "Re: GuiGFX Library!"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 14 Nov 1998 22:09:06 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk>
Date: Sat, 14 Nov 1998 22:05:25 +0000
Subject: Re: GuiGFX Library!

Warning: This is a message in MIME format. Your mail reader does not
support MIME. Some parts of this message will be readable as plain text.
To see the rest, you will need to upgrade your mail reader.


--BOUNDARY.1747596584.3

Centro Amiga churned out *this* drivel :

> Yes, yes, yes!!! Can someone do it??? It`s driving me nuts to have to
> program in C just to use this kind of things. If we had someway of doing
it
> in Blitz it would be much easier. Just picture not having to worry with
> screen depth, colour reduction,...... I feel that the moment someone
brings
> this kind of libs into Blitz lots of Image Processors and the like will
> surface.
> 

Well,here are the converted libraries. I've got them numbered as :

    guigfx.library1 - 5
    render.library1 - 7

The readme for guigfx.library says you need render.library, so I've
converted that as well :)

You may need to change the library numbers for your system - use
BlitzLibMan, which you can get from :
    
    ftp://x2ftp.oulu.fi/pub/amiga/prog/blitz/blitzlibman.lha

BTW If you want to convert libraries easily,use BlitzLibMan, and my
"conversion" of fdconvert - Aminet - dev/basic/newfdconvert.lha ...it's
easy! 

Just find a free lib number with BlitzLibMan, and use that number for the 
NewFDConverted library...

The commands tokenise here, though I'm not even gonna attempt to understand
how to use 'em ;)

Get the autodocs from the archives on Aminet...

Oh,yeah - throw these libraries into your Blitzlibs/amigalibs drawer...

See ya,
-- 
James L Boyd - Team *AMIGA*
jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk
------------------------------------------------------------------
"I want to hear the holy rampage/I don't mind a little ear damage" 
- Frank Black,"I Want Rock 'n' Roll" ( www.goodnoise.com )

