I just joined in this list. I've been blitz-user only few week so I MAY have a lot of questions in future:-| At the moment I'm trying to open a screen with a bit different bitmap-structure than usual but somehow it does not work. Could someone help me with this one:
I want to display a low-res screen with 4 bitplanes.Bitplane addresses should be like this - bitplane1 - addr
bitplane2 - addr+40
bitplane3 - addr+80
bitplane4 - addr+120, and both bitplane-modulos should be set to 120
As far as I know it isn't possible to first create a bitplane (Bitplane 0,320,160,4) and then reset bitplane-pointers so I've used a bank as bitplanes. Here's what I have got:
...
Wbstartup
Closeed
Nocli

Initbank 1,25600,2			;25600 = 40*160*4
START.l = peek.l(addr bank(1))		;Start-address of bank

Cop$=mki$($108)+mki$(120)		;Modulos 	
Cop$+mki$($10a)+mki$(120)
