Hello all
	Recently I became stuck with this problem.  I know how to 
hide the mouse pointer (ie make a blank shape and set the mouse 
for that) but how do I get the mouse pointer back?

Steven



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_235" "Re: Hiding the pointer"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    10 Nov 98 10:20:20 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 10 Nov 1998 10:20:04 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Hiding the pointer

On 10 Nov 98, at 10:15, S.J.CROY wrote:

> 
> Hello all
>  Recently I became stuck with this problem.  I know how to 
> hide the mouse pointer (ie make a blank shape and set the mouse 
> for that) but how do I get the mouse pointer back?
> 

ClearPointer_ Peek.l(Addr Window(#winnum)) will restore it to the 
default Workbench pointer, if you have a custom pointer then you 
should do the same as what you did to set it up in the first place.




|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
