@NODE "Mail_242" "Re: How to format a string ?"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    23 Nov 98 09:31:39 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 09:31:33 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: How to format a string ?

On 20 Nov 98, at 15:34, M. Misic wrote:

> i have a problem and don't know how to fix it.
> 
> I've a program, that reads a string by #ReadSerialString#.
> Now, the string which i get, includes CR's and LF's.
> When printing that string to a window, the CR's and LF's will printed as
> such.
> 
> How do i make it, that each CR or LF will be executet as newline-charact=
er
> ?

 Try going through each character and filtering out the CR or LF 
(can't remember which one Chr$(10) is:

; a$ is the string from ReadSerialString
b$ =3D ""
For i.w=3D1 to Len(a$)
    If(Mid$(a$,i,1) <> Chr$(10))
        b$ =3D b$ + Mid$(a$,i,1)
    Endif
Next


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694


