@NODE "Mail_252" "Re: I solved the "real" problem: Bug in EFMUILib"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Wed, 11 Nov 1998 09:28:13 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: I solved the "real" problem: Bug in EFMUILib
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Andreas, =


> The problem that I complained yesterday on the list is caused by EFMUI
Lib.
> =

> If you open more than 14 mui window objects your application will crash=

> sooner
> or later. =

> =

> I attach some source to this mail. You can run it as many times as you
like
> it. It won`t
> crash. But if you then uncomment the two lines which open the 15th wind=
ow,
> it`ll
> crash after two or three compiles. It would be very kind of you if anyo=
ne
> could test
> this -- because the problem is still a strange one and I want to know i=
f
> it`s only on
> my amiga.

    Hum, in fact it crash with any windows, not only MUI ones. On the
AmigaOS, each task can only have 16 windows opened with a different msgpo=
rt
for each. The solution is easy but not well know from Amiga coders: use t=
he
same userport for each windows (it's knows as shared msgport). You need a=

special close routine which look in the msg queued and remove all which a=
re
for the window which will be close.

    Another problem I've got while writting TheBoss :-)

    Bye,
 =

                        Fred.

