@NODE "Mail_259" "Re: Intuifont-problems"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    10 Nov 98 12:00:19 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 10 Nov 1998 12:00:09 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Intuifont-problems

On 10 Nov 98, at 10:28, M. Misic wrote:

> i've some trouble using intuifont.
> 
> When i do something like that:
> 
> #Use Screen# 0
> *Scr=3D#ActiveScreen#
> FH=3D#Peek#.w(#Pee#k.l(*Scr+40)+4)
> FN$=3D#Peek$#(#Pee#k.l(*Scr+40)+8
> #LoadFont# 0,FN$,FH
> #Use Untuifont# 0
> 
> At compiletime i get the message "can't load font" and compiling stops.
> But when i create an executable directly all will be fine...
> 
> Any ideas ?

 You don't get errors like that at compile time. Do you mean if you 
run the program from inside Blitz? It could be a problem with your 
screen code. If its something like WBToScreen 0 then it will find the 
workbench screen and use its font. However, if its FindScreen 0 then 
that tries to use the frontmost screen (I think) which would be Ted.

 Ted probably doesn't set a screen font in its screen structure or 
something equally stupid.

 Try printing the name and size of the font before you try to open 
it. If its "" then that'll be why you can't open it.

 And life's a lot easier if you use the proper structures ratehr than 
peeks.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694


@ENDNODE
