Both should visit the site of Redmond ...



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_262" "Re: Intuifont-problems"
From: Luca Carminati <toffi@spm.it>
Date: Tue, 10 Nov 1998 19:23:05 -0500
Subject: Re: Intuifont-problems
Encoding: quoted-printable

On 10-Nov-98, M. Misic wrote:

>Hi Blizzers,

>i've some trouble using intuifont.

>When i do something like that:

>#Use Screen# 0
>*Scr=3D#ActiveScreen#
>FH=3D#Peek#.w(#Pee#k.l(*Scr+40)+4)
>FN$=3D#Peek$#(#Pee#k.l(*Scr+40)+8
>#LoadFont# 0,FN$,FH
>#Use Untuifont# 0

>At compiletime i get the message "can't load font" and compiling stops.
>But when i create an executable directly all will be fine...

>Any ideas ?

Hi,

are you sure the line 'FN$=3DPeek$(Peek.l(*Scr+40)+8' is correct? It seem=
s it
doesn't point to the font name. Try substituting it with
'FN$=3DPeek$(Peek.l(Peek.l(*Scr+40)))'. Here it works fine with the TED s=
creen
too.

Or you could do the following:

  FindScreen 0

  *Scr.Screen=3DPeek.l(Addr Screen(0))
  FontName$=3DPeek$(*Scr\Font\ta_Name)
  FontSize.w=3D*Scr\Font\ta_YSize
  LoadFont 0,FontName$,FontSize

You need 'amigalibs.res' for this.

C ya...




-- =

Best regards,

Luca.

   _____________________________________
  |                                     |
