@NODE "Mail_264" "It's rude to point!!!"
From: S9225796 <S9225796@Rothervalley.ac.uk>
Subject: It's rude to point!!!
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 10:42:02 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Dodgy Pointers

Firstly, thanx to Luca, Gigandet, Vincent and everyone else who sent me
suggestions on how to change the mouse pointer into a busy pointer,
however
I wonder if you could help me with this beast of a problem.

The first time i used the codes to change to pointer to a busy one, they
worked fine, and so, for most of the day I went about adding busy
pointers into many of my programs. However, the next day when I loaded
the progams back into Blitz2 and ran them, they all crashed!, often
seriously and causing my hard disk to re-validate. 

This problem is busy pointer related, and I know this because when I
disable the routines the programs work fine, however this crash is very
random. Sometimes the pointers change, and other times it crashes my
system. Does anyone know why this is happerning to me?

Below is my code, and I am using the `AmigaLibs.res':

  ;Setup Busy Pointer
  Statement busypointer{win.b}
    Dim pointer.TagItem(2)
    pointer(1)\ti_Tag=#WA_BusyPointer,True
    pointer(2)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE,0
    If SetWindowPointerA_(Peek.l(Addr Window(win)),&pointer(1))
    EndIf
  End Statement

  ;Setup Normal Pointer
  Statement normpointer{win.b}
    Dim pointer.TagItem(2)
    pointer(1)\ti_Tag=#WA_BusyPointer,False
    pointer(2)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE,0
    If SetWindowPointerA_(Peek.l(Addr Window(win)),&pointer(1))
    EndIf
  End Statement

*To activate a busy pointer I do this: 

  busypointer{1}

*To activate a normal pointer I do this:

  normpointer{1}


The code above, on my system, is about as stable as an alcoholic with a
pint of beer in his hand! Does anyone else have any problems like this?

Also, (sorry 'bout the massive e-mail!) Which de-bugger is everyone
using? I am still using the small & original debugger, which appears to
be a useless defence against major errors, and bloody busy pointers etc.
Just take a look at my crashy history file for one day! :

