@NODE "Mail_265" "Re: It's rude to point!!!"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 23 Nov 1998 14:21:52 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 13:56:03 +0000
Subject: Re: It's rude to point!!!

Hi,

> Below is my code, and I am using the `AmigaLibs.res':
>  Statement busypointer{win.b}
>    Dim pointer.TagItem(2)
>    pointer(1)\ti_Tag=#WA_BusyPointer,True
>    pointer(2)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE,0
>    If SetWindowPointerA_(Peek.l(Addr Window(win)),&pointer(1))
>    EndIf
>  End Statement

> The code above, on my system, is about as stable as an alcoholic with a
> pint of beer in his hand! Does anyone else have any problems like this?

I can't see why you're having problems with the above code. It worked
okay for me.

I reworked the two statements and merged them into one single statement
which uses the Blitz window structure instead of the Peek. I honestly don't
think it makes any difference but it's always nice to see structures rather
than peeks. I also used SetWindowPointer_ as a statement rather than
a function (without the If and the () )

here it is...

Statement BusyPointer{win.b,busy.b}
  Dim tags.TagItem(2)
  tags(0)\ti_Tag=#WA_BusyPointer,busy      ; (True or False)
  tags(1)\ti_Tag=#TAG_DONE,0
  *win.window=Addr Window(win)    ; blitz window (bb2objtypes.res !! )
  SetWindowPointerA_ *win\_window,&tags(0)
End Statement

Maybe (just maybe) you'll have more luck with this version but I
honestly can't see there being much difference. Unless someone
can spot a sneaky problem in these statements I'd suggest you
take a look at another possible problem.

> Also, (sorry 'bout the massive e-mail!) Which de-bugger is everyone
> using? I am still using the small & original debugger, which appears to
> be a useless defence against major errors, and bloody busy pointers etc.
> Just take a look at my crashy history file for one day! :
> Ten crashes by Blitz2 in one day. mmmm. Not bad, I have had worse :)

I'm using the RED Debugger v2.5 which comes with Blitz Support Suite.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

"Do you recognise this man? Look at the front of his head."
-- Brass Eye



