I use a version similar to Paul's, also with no problems.  Maybe the "If"
part is what's causing the problem?  

SetWindowPointerA_ is really a statement - it doesn't return a value for the
If...
> 
>> Also, (sorry 'bout the massive e-mail!) Which de-bugger is everyone
