@NODE "Mail_267" "Re: It's rude to point!!!"
          Paris Tue, 24 Nov 1998 00:06:35 +0100 (MET)
          Paris Tue, 24 Nov 1998 00:06:31 +0100 (MET)
From: Gigandet Jean-Marc <HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 23:18:48 +0100
Subject: Re: It's rude to point!!!
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello,

You didn't use the code I sent ...
Take a look at the way I do it, you'll notice some differences.
First I'm not sure SetWindowPointerA_ does work with a TagItem structure =
with this syntax (it returns a value), but it works with a TagList (that'=
s what Blitz help gives, TagItem is an array, not TagList).
Second, because you use a TagItem, you must use an ampersand, and so you =
use an adress not a structure.
Third, to setup normal pointer, it's faster and more efficient to use Cle=
arPointer_ ...
Try my method. It works fine on lot of A1200 and A4000, and had never cau=
se any troubles.

Regards
-- =

HURRICAN@wanadoo.fr
