@NODE "Mail_287" "Mildred 1.13"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 26 Nov 1998 21:42:11 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 26 Nov 98 21:38:34 +0000
Subject: Mildred 1.13
Encoding: 7bit

Hi folks.

v1.13 of the lib has just been uploaded, should be on-line soon. I've
added 8 new commands:

MBox
MBoxShape
MBoxStencil
MBoxCookie
MBoxF
MBoxFShape
MBoxFStencil
MBoxFCookie

Btw, I was wondering, does anyone use the `-1' colour option of the
graphics routines in blitz, to do inverse? I know it might come in use
in things like a paint program, for rubber-banding etc. If there is
demand for it I'll add it in.

Drawing boxes to stencils and cookies will render a /representation/
of the given colour, into the stencil or cookie, not the actual colour
itself. Technically, colour 0 would put $FF into the cookie, and
anything else would put $00 there.

Also it is faster to use MBoxF to draw 1-column areas than MBox,
because MBox draws left and right pixels whereas MBox only draws one
pixel per line.

And I haven't gone for the blitz syntax, so the operands are:

X1,Y1,Width,Height[,Colour]

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_288" "Mildred 1.15"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sat, 28 Nov 1998 20:25:23 +0000
From: "Paul" <paulwest@stationone.demon.co.uk>
Organization: private
Date: 28 Nov 98 20:12:26 +0000
Subject: Mildred 1.15
Encoding: 7bit

Hiya.

Mildred 1.15 is now ready and there has been a significant improvement
to the planar-to-chunky speed. It is now 200% faster and could
possibly convert a 320x240 area at 25fps on an 060/50.

A new command, MGenericPtr has been added, to which you should pass
the parameters Xpos.w,Ypos.w,BaseAddress.l,RowWidth.w. It calculates
an address based on the base address, plus the offset of the xpos,ypos
coordinates. Width of the memory area is needed to calculate the
coordinate offset. This can be used for things such as the Planar.l
parameter of Mc2p and of MPlanar16ToBitmap p2c conversion where
RowWidth.w would be the width of the planar bitmap, and BaseAddress.l
would be the base address of the planar memory.

Also MBlit, MBlock, MQBlit, MQBlock, MSBlit, MSBlock, MQSBlit and
MQSBlock now unconditionally use a shape's handle when working out
where to output it to. Care should be taken to ensure that the
combination of Xpos and XHandle, or Ypos and YHandle does not exceed
signed word values, which hopefully isn't very likely.

-- 
Paul.

IRC: #amiga, Dalnet: #blitz
WWW: http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk
E-M: paul@stationone.demon.co.uk



@ENDNODE
