>     Seems to be an excellent work. More impressions will come later...

You'll give me a big head! :-) I've been doing some examples also and
they are uploaded to the support site. Thing is that the proxy cache
thingy at demon doesn't always seem to update stuff, which is the
whole point of it being a cache, but it should appear soon.

Also I have so far found 3 bugs since posting the lib to the list.
Current version is now 1.12 and is also on the support site, but again
it hasn't appeared yet (when I last checked).

I haven't done any more to the documentation yet but using it myself
I'm finding it quite easy to get into. I hadn't actually done much
with it myself apart from primitive bug-hunting tests. It's close
enough in accordance with what you already know of blitz's routines
that I am hoping example programs will speak greater volumes than
in-depth documentation, so I look forward to seeing your experiments.

