@NODE "Mail_294" "Re: Mildred library"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Thu, 26 Nov 1998 13:47:12 +1200
Subject: Re: Mildred library

On 25-Nov-98, Paul wrote:
>Hi blitzers.

>Here is a new library for your programming pleasure (see attatched
>archive). This is not the promised `Junior' version, but instead this
>is the FULL library.
 
  Yeee- haaa!!! :)  Alright, now we can easily write games that run
through the OS, and it should be easy to convert the routines to a new
OS/CPU (whatever it ends up being :)
  I saw the beauty of being able to do this while playing Quake on the
PPC the other day- you just hit left-Amiga M to flip screens, and have
full access to the machine and internet, while Quake is happily running
multi-player through the internet at the same time!! You can't really do
that as nicely on a PC as Quake apparently runs like a pig in a Window-
I assume some apps can run on a PC under interrupt at the same time
(with Quake in full screen mode), but it's not the same, and would Quake
freeze if you flipped back to Windows?  Note: I'm not intending to cause
a PC vs Amiga thread here- it's just an observation on OS games on a
decent machine. Please keep any responses rational and on topic :)
 
-- 
        Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz> ICQ #15349462 
      



