@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_300" "Re: More OS friendly stuff"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 5 Nov 1998 01:46:32 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Wed, 04 Nov 1998 21:16:32 +0000
Subject: Re: More OS friendly stuff

Hi,

> Use Screens and not Windows for the OS friendly game.
> Windows are impossibly slow and you just can't do db on them.

If you're going for AGA/ECS only then Screens are an nice
easy-to-use option. However, it's not very system friendly as
far as rtg support goes. Using Windows is a great way to give
your game gfx-card support and if you're working in chunky
modes like Doom it's also very fast. After saying all that, there
are hundreds of ways to render a games display and there are
always many things to consider so it's not easy to choose the
best method.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - burkey.home.ml.org >



@ENDNODE
