@NODE "Mail_313" "Re: MUI stuff + sound sound stuff !!"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 20 Nov 1998 21:07:28 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Nov 1998 21:34:05 +0000
Subject: Re: MUI stuff + sound sound stuff !!

Hi,

> 2) Evreyone seems to have done a lot of work on GFX card stuff (for which
> I'm very grateful) but has anyone done any work on custom sound routines??
> As you're well aware BLITZ doesn't let you play samples in memory over
> 128k. Any custom sounds routines anyone?

It's probably worth moving over to AHI support for this kind of
thing although I'm sure the ahi.device support is prety much the
same as audio.device support If you want an example of how
to support AHI you could try my AHIFuncs archive on my projects
web page.

http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk/projects.html

As for writing your own routines it's probably not worth reinventing
the wheel when AHI gives you so many advantages like big samples,
sound card support, samples in fast mem, extra sound channels,
extra volume/stereo control, 8/14/16bit sound support. It's also
very easy to use.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

