@NODE "Mail_318" "Re: Need some help about promotion display mode."
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 2 Nov 1998 21:22:33 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 02 Nov 1998 20:34:46 +0000
Subject: Re: Need some help about promotion display mode.

Hi,

> I want to use display library with VGA/promotion display mode.I have look
> some documentation about news AGA registers, but i'haven't find anything.
> Can somebody Help me?

What does VGA/Promotion mean? if you're trying to open a screen
can can be promoted to other modes then you should use the OS
rather than the hardware bashing display library. The ScreenTags
command is the best way to open screens without resorting to the
intuition.library and can be promoted if you don't bother providing
a screen mode requester instead.

Cheers,

-- 
<- Paul Burkey <-> http://burkey.home.ml.org ->



