@NODE "Mail_320" "re: New Amiga rumours"
          with SMTP id <19981104002725.TZW6156@ameritech.net>
          for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Tue, 3 Nov 1998 18:27:25 -0600
From: pkocourek@ameritech.net (Paul Kocourek)
Date: Tue, 03 Nov 1998 18:32:13
Subject: re: New Amiga rumours
Organization: None (sh82)
X-Receipt: No
X-Form: Standard.FORM

You know, would it not be great if Amiga Inc. could just
bring the new Amiga out
THIS year?  Why do we have to keep waiting...and waiting...and
waiting...and waiting...???

I'd just about cut off my good arm for a new Amiga NOW, if
only to shut up the idiots who
own PCs and think they are the greatest things to ever operate
off an electric power line.

When the Amiga came out, it blew away PCs and Macs.  PC users
sniffed down their
stuck-up noses at the Amiga, dismissing it as a game machine,
not a "real" computer.  Now, the
hottest computers being sold today in the PC market are--are
you ready for this--game machines!

What foppish idiots.  What moronic hypocrites.  Oh well,
you get the idea.

Now, don't get the wrong idea, those of you out there who
own and/or use PCs.  I am a M.I.S. for my company
and handle the company's PCs and the Novell network.  Maybe
PCs have faster processors (for now), but does
Windows ever suck!  It takes forever to boot, and crashes
all the time for no apparent reason whatsoever.  Given
that Windows 98 "fixes" 5000!! bugs in Window 95, you wonder
how many are still there, and how many new ones
were created in Win98.  My A1200 w/ 68030 @ 50Mhz is way
more stable, and I get things done on the machine.

However, the grim reality is, most programs are available
only for PCs.  I plan to buy a PC for this despicable
reason, but there's no way around it.  Where the heck is
Amiga Inc, and why are they sitting on their hands?

Blitz is a great language, and once we FINALLY get out new
machines, I truly hope Blitz will lead the way in programming
for the new Amiga.  I hope we can all hang in there 'til
then.

Best to you all.

What are the rest of you Blitzers using for monitors?  The
only monitors being sold here in the
USA are modified NTSC Philips televisions, for crying out
loud!  I want a monitor that can use
ALL my Amiga's video modes.  

--



@ENDNODE
