@NODE "Mail_322" "re: New Amiga rumours"
 Wed, 4 Nov 1998 18:11:33 +0100
Date: Wed, 04 Nov 1998 18:10:33 +0100
From: stifter@mira.cz
Subject: re: New Amiga rumours

>However, the grim reality is, most programs are available
>only for PCs.  I plan to buy a PC for this despicable

Cheap solution: Using UAE. It is said to be slow to emulate all those Amiga
                functions like copper instructions, playing four samples 
                each with different frequency is also difficult to emulate
on PC
                soundcards. It's slow but doable.

My solution: An Amiga connected to PC with a screengrabber so both can run
             and coexist in a true multitasking environment ;)

Better solution: An Inside Out card in a PC - Amiga on a PCI card, using
                 PC's resources i.e.HDD, FDD, CD etc. using the PC's
graphic card
                 for display.


So both wayz i can enjoy programming Blitz at work ;) (do not call my Boss!)
or doing my work the efficient way on Amiga then transferring the result
to IBM compastible.



