Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 3 Nov 1998 09:30:28 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: New Amiga Rumours - The End

 A brief summary, so we can put this baby to sleep.

- All current processors are crap, all future processors are crap, 
we'd be as well taking some mindbending drugs and plugging our heads 
into our monitors. Lets face it, if Intel and Motorola were to design 
totally new, no restriction processors tomorrow, they'd probably come 
up with exactly the same specs, except that Intels byte order would 
be backwards.

- iMac, PC, Amiga =3D Scissors, paper, stone. Each one pisses over the 
other, but not all the time.

- Your amount of memory doesn't matter if your OS supports virtual 
memory properly, although a generous base amount is useful (32Mb+).

- None of this rubbish matters because according to AF, Wierd Science 
and everyone else who tries to lie to us, digital convergance is the 
future. In laymans terms, every computer is going to be the same, and 
run all software. Ever written. But lets not stop at computers, lets 
go the whole hog and make everybody Borg. Everything will be the same 
after that.






