Hi,

 For a start, Amiga users never really did put up with 2 meg (not the serious
users). You need at least 6 meg to get the basic progs running at decent level
(i started with 8), like Wordworth, decent Workbench etc.

 But if you don't want to have to close down programs and just generally be
able to use your computer properly, 32 meg is needed..

 If you a gfx artist, you need the big 256meg machines etc.

 Workbench isn't as brilliant as it started off as, it is starting to die out
a bit, but Workbench 4 should prove to be cool...

 Windows 98 only REALLY needs 8 meg of ram, which isn't much, but it caches
everything and speeds things up a lot, thank god we still aren't in the age of
020's!

 Amiga will never catch up with graphics, its been out of the picture for too
long.

 Pity.

 And amiga's use the same amount of RAM, if you want to play doom, your need
at least 4 meg or something, same as PC.

 If you want to play Myst, you need 8 meg of ram, Napalm needs 16 (will when
its out), like C&C needs it in high res etc...

 The amiga only used less ram because the stuff it was doing was never as
complex or had as much graphics.

 Jamie Bentley

 I hate PCs but they are, you MUST admit, fast, efficient, and increadibly
easy to hack :)



