Hi,

While we're off topix.... as a PPC user I am completely
worn out in terms of worrying about the Amiga.  Basically the PPC
cards are very expensive fpus. All I've used it for is to play Doom!
There is little professional software
out on it and the future is bleak. Exciting new hardware like that needs a
broad range of software to give it a launch. Phase5 have now gone off to
concentrate on the *MAC* so future PPC development is doubtful. Amiga didn't
help by throwing doubts about  the PPC
earlier on in the year and then changing there minds again, OR HAVE THEY?,
we don't know -  both Phase5 and Amiga are guilty of withholding
their intentions from all of us so we cannot take their word or anyones for
anything.  I'm just going to wait and see. No one knows. I'm not bothered
either anymore, I'm going to use my Amiga for now and Amiga Inc and phase5
or whoever can mess about as long as they like for all I care.
If I sound bored its cos I am ;)

Alex Smyth



