> new features too. Any requests for features? :)

 You've probably already go this but: huge numbers of simultaneous 
players (either on one machine) or across network. With a networked 
one, you could have multi screen arenas, as everyone will have a 
separate display.
 DynaBlaster was great as 5-player, and the insane tune that played 
was sooooo addictive.

> Thanks! Mildred is possibly the best library extension for Blitz I've se=
en
> yet. I have yet to try it but the commands available are certainly
> impressive.  I have an 040 and unfortunately it looks like this will be
> the minimum cpu required to play my game. 

 ??? WHAT ???
 040 min spec for a DynaBlaster game (sorry if I've made your game 
sound small) but that seems a bit excessive. If you've got a lot of 
"extra" flashy effects like every pixel of a bomb exploding being 
calculated in a 3D space then plotted with texture mapping and Gourad 
shading, then maybe you could only call these routines if you detect 
a certain processor (or above).

 Unless I'm totally wrong and its actually a first-person 
perspective/Quake/Doom type of DynaBlaster :) That would be cool.


