Yes I know it sounds fairly ridiculous. However since the game is currently
written in 99% Blitz rather than pure assembler it is slower than games
like dynablasters. Also the graphics are in 256 colours, the game
multitasks and uses chunky2planar on machines without a graphics card so
this slows it down some more. Not to mention having to draw lots of huge
bombs exploding at once means updating most of the screen.
 
> Unless I'm totally wrong and its actually a first-person 
