@NODE "Mail_391" "Passing Esc Chars"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 12 Nov 1998 16:14:11 +0000
From: Daniel Allsopp <slash@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 12 Nov 1998 16:14:04 +0000
Subject: Passing Esc Chars

Hi all,

I'm writing an MUI program and I want to PreParse a TextBox. The AutoDocs
say you pass the string pointer of the ESC controls.

    MuiAddTags 10,#MUIA_Text_PreParse,Null("\33b")

Should make any text in the text object appear in bold but it doesn't.

Also if I try it the other way and put the control codes into the string
they just get printed instead of being used.

    MuiSet 10,#MUIA_Text_Contents,Null("Hello \33bEveryone\33n")

Should print Everyone in BOLD, but it just print the \33b and \33n commands
too!!


-- 
Cheers,
    Daniel

<tsb>E-Mail: slash@thesnakepit.demon.co.uk
<tsb>URL: http://www.thesnakepit.demon.co.uk/
<tsb>



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_392" "Re: Passing Esc Chars"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    12 Nov 98 16:28:22 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Thu, 12 Nov 1998 16:28:07 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Passing Esc Chars

On 12 Nov 98, at 16:14, Daniel Allsopp wrote:

> Hi all,
> 
> I'm writing an MUI program and I want to PreParse a TextBox. The AutoDoc=
s
> say you pass the string pointer of the ESC controls.
> 
>     MuiAddTags 10,#MUIA_Text_PreParse,Null("\33b")
> 
> Should make any text in the text object appear in bold but it doesn't.
> 
> Also if I try it the other way and put the control codes into the string
> they just get printed instead of being used.
> 
>     MuiSet 10,#MUIA_Text_Contents,Null("Hello \33bEveryone\33n")

 That would work in C, as the \ character in a string means insert 
the following character (ASCII) code. And don't use Null, Blitz 
stores it strings with a null terminator from v1.7 up or something. 
So what you want to do is have something like

MuiSet 
10,#MUIA_Text_Contents,"Hello"+chr$(33)+"bEverybody"+chr$(33)+"n"

but obviously on one line, damn this program.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694


@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_393" "Re: Passing Esc Chars"
From: Rui Carvalho <grim@ip.pt>
Date: Thu, 12 Nov 1998 19:33:41 +0000
Organization: Dark Dreams Designs
Subject: Re: Passing Esc Chars
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello David

Somewhere David Mcminn wrote:

DM > That would work in C, as the \ character in a string means insert =

DM > the following character (ASCII) code. And don't use Null, Blitz =

DM > stores it strings with a null terminator from v1.7 up or something. =

DM > So what you want to do is have something like

DM > MuiSet =

DM > 10,#MUIA_Text_Contents,"Hello"+chr$(33)+"bEverybody"+chr$(33)+"n"

DM > but obviously on one line, damn this program.

Sorry but it doesn't work... It's 33 in Oct in decimal use chr$(27)..

Thanks for the tip, it solved my problem too ;^)

-- =

Best Regards,
