@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_394" "Re: Passing Esc Chars"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
	Blitz Mailing List <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>
Date: Fri, 13 Nov 1998 11:45:00 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Passing Esc Chars

I watched as Daniel Allsopp hammered "Passing Esc Chars" out on their
keyboard...

DA> I'm writing an MUI program and I want to PreParse a TextBox. The
AutoDocs
DA> say you pass the string pointer of the ESC controls.

DA>    MuiAddTags 10,#MUIA_Text_PreParse,Null("\33b")

DA> Should make any text in the text object appear in bold but it
doesn't.

DA> Also if I try it the other way and put the control codes into the
string
DA> they just get printed instead of being used.

DA>    MuiSet 10,#MUIA_Text_Contents,Null("Hello \33bEveryone\33n")

DA> Should print Everyone in BOLD, but it just print the \33b and \33n
commands
DA> too!!

That's because the \33 means that actual escape character, which in
Blitz is chr$(27)....so that last string should be "Hello
"+chr$(27)+"bEveryone"+chr$(27)+"n"

-- 
