@NODE "Mail_396" "PC Vs Amiga, Put a stop to it!"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Thu, 5 Nov 1998 13:39:50 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Thu, 05 Nov 1998 13:05:52 +0000
Subject: PC Vs Amiga, Put a stop to it!

Hi,

The computer market is prety huge now with many systems to
choose from. The x86 based PC system with Windows is only
one of many choices. What use is there in going on and on
about how bad the Windows platform is? We might as well
argue about how the SGI market is bad for games or how the
Atari ST sucks now that the market is full of music software.
I have many friends who are designer and artists, most of
them find the Mac is a ferfect platform for them. I won't even
go into consoles, linux, NT, OS2, BeOS, Acorn's and whatever
other systems and os's there are.

I recently discovered the huge benefits of owning a PC and
running Windows. If course the OS isn't as good as AmigaOS
and of course it's not always easy to config the hardware. I'm
still happy to be using the Amiga and I will continue to abuse
the Amigas good points but if the Amiga could do everything I
needed I wouln't have to get my hands dirty in the Pea Sea.

So whats the point in bashing the bad points about all these
systems when they all have their good points. Even the Atari
is a better choice than Amiga in some areas but what is the
point in discussing it? This is an exclusive Amiga group so
there's no need to advocate the Amiga so lets stop it! :)

I won't mention the arguments about the latest rumours. Lets
all wait for somthing real to happen and then we can give it
a jolly good bashing if need be! :)

Cheers

-- 
< Paul Burkey - burkey.home.ml.org >



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_397" "Re: PC Vs Amiga, Put a stop to it!"
