@NODE "Mail_406" "Re: Planar 2 Chunky"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Sun, 22 Nov 1998 16:39:05 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: Re: Planar 2 Chunky
Encoding: quoted-printable

    Hi Paul, =


> I need to convert an 8bit planar bitmap to chunky. So far I'm
> using a basic Poke() and Point() method that converts a planar
> bitmap of 640x480 in less than 2 seconds (89 ticks) on my 040.
> This conversion isn't required in a real-time situation so 2
> seconds isn't too bad but if anyone has a faster Point() command
> or a faster method altogether let me know!

    First, you should use the NPoke() routine which is about 20% faster t=
han
the original Poke routine or better, use this little tricks to poke into
memory:

    NewType .byte      ;  =

        byte.b            ; Change to the value to poke =

    End NewType        ;
     =

    Deftype .byte *a

; After, init *a to your memory location, and poke with the standard meth=
od
;
 =

    *a =3D *ChunkyBuffer
    *a\byte =3D YourValueToPoke : *a+1 ; Increase your position of 1
    =

    This method is even faster than the standard NPoke() routine. You can=

use this trick to Peek.s()  =


    Value =3D *a\byte =


                        Fred.

