If only it were that simple! To cut a long story short, I recently rewrote
all of the graphics routines used in my "hit game ;)" Foundation. Now all
graphics are rendered in full chunky mode. The only problem is, the CD
contains about 100 meg graphics in planar format. So, I can use
planar 2 chunky convertion when the graphics are loaded or I supply
100meg of graphics with the next update :) In all honesty the problem
isn't bad at all. The only bit that is slow is the part when it loads one of
the full screen renders. It takes just under 2 seconds to load them. Most
people wouldn't notice an extra 2 seconds here and there but I'm a
perfectionist 'aint I? :)

