Hi,

why not use a RAW file and use Stonecracker to compress it. The compression
is pretty good, and reasonably fast. The resulting Stonecracked RAW file
has, so far, always been smaller than the IFF file for me. The RedBlitzLibs
contain Stonecracker decrunching code. Palettes need to be saved separately,
though. PPaint can save RAW files. If anyone wants an example code to load a
crunched RAW file and display it I would be happy to post some. The same
thing can, by the way, be done for shapes. Just a thought.


