A Quake server can be run in 3 different modes, if you limit the game
to 4 players, one of those players can act as a server.  However, ID
reccomend that if you have more than 4 players you use a dedicated
mode which will allow 16 players, although the server cannot not be
used to enter the game (17 machines in total).

However, there is another mode that allows 16 players, but without
having to dedicate the server. Meaning that the server can still be
used to play on, although it specifies that you shouldn't do this
unless you have a fast machine.

I'm not sure how it deals with the person playing on the server, I
just presume it's built into the code somehow instead of having to
open another port and connect.

