@NODE "Mail_433" "Re: PPC C2P"
From: Anton Reinauer <anton@ww.co.nz>
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 15:16:38 +1200
Subject: Re: PPC C2P

On 23-Nov-98, Rick Hodger wrote:

>I'm not sure how it deals with the person playing on the server, I
>just presume it's built into the code somehow instead of having to
>open another port and connect.
 
  It sends all messages out the same as if it were sending it to another
player but loops them back to itself- it works the same in one-player
mode. They say it's best to have a dedicated Server, as it's fairer, as
the person on the server has no lag in their player's movements, like
the other players's do.

