@NODE "Mail_438" "Printing on Bitmaps"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    1 Dec 98 09:27:45 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 1 Dec 1998 09:27:37 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Printing on Bitmaps

'ello crazy peeps,

 OK, I got the program working for printing text to a bitmap. Just 
needed to use +8 in the SetFont_ line. Whats the workaround for the 
third parameter of statements getting screwed up (or what causes it). 
Because it affects the code below on my version of Blitz?


;8<-----8<-----8<-----8<-----8<-----8<-----8<-----
#BMPWIDTH =3D 320
#BMPHEIGHT =3D 256

WBStartup
DEFTYPE.w

LoadFont 0,"ufolarge.font",15

BitMap 0,#BMPWIDTH,#BMPHEIGHT,3
For i.w=3D0 To 200
  Line Rnd(#BMPWIDTH),Rnd(#BMPHEIGHT),Rnd(#BMPWIDTH),Rnd(#BMPHEIGHT),3
Next

; Prints only the foreground of some text to the currently used bitmap
; in the currently used intuifont. The string text is printed at
; co-ordinates
; x,y in the colour col. Whats the workaround for the third parameter
; of statements being wrong. Tell me now!!
Statement FGPrint{text.s, x.w, why.w, y.w, col.w}
    DEFTYPE._RastPort rp

    InitRastPort_ &rp
    rp\_BitMap =3D Addr BitMap(Used BitMap)
    SetFont_ &rp,Peek.l(Addr IntuiFont(Used IntuiFont) + 8)
    SetDrMd_ &rp,#JAM1
    SetAPen_ &rp,col
    Move_ &rp,x,y
    Text_ &rp,&text,Len(text)
End Statement

FGPrint{"Bite me",#BMPWIDTH/2,0,40,5}
Screen 0,0,0,#BMPWIDTH,#BMPHEIGHT,3,0,"e",0,1,0
ClickMouse
End


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
  http://members.xoom.xom/David_McMinn


@ENDNODE
