@NODE "Mail_440" "Re: Problem with Paul's AHI example"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Nov 1998 11:00:58 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: Problem with Paul's AHI example

I watched as Toby Zuijdveld hammered "Problem with Paul's AHI example"
out on their keyboard...

TZ> I reduced #MAX_SAMPS to 2 and set AHI's Audio Mode to 8bit mono,
4000khz... 
TZ> in the hope of reducing the size of any needed AHIbuffer, but
still no good. 
TZ> AHI _can_ use chip, too, if it's out of fast, right?

Nope, that's the whole point of copying the samples into Fast mem,
when the samples are loaded into chip AHI doesn't play anything and
the play command returns instantly.

TZ> 1) Am I doing something wrong?  (I havn't edited the sources)

Nope.

TZ> 2) How much contiguous fast mem does AHI #NEED# to set itself up?

Dunno.

TZ> 3) How much mem gets eaten up by AHI for each sample info?  
TZ>      (#MAX_SAMPS)

ATM it stops at 128kb, because the sounds are loaded with "LoadSound"
into chip mem, and then copied over to Fast mem, the LoadSound command
limits the samples to 128kb.

-- 
<sb>Rick Hodger - Programmer for #Pagan Software#
