@NODE "Mail_446" "Re: RAM=HD to Rick Hodger"
From: Stephen Fellner <sfell@xtra.co.nz>
Date: Fri, 06 Nov 1998 20:42:08 +1200
Subject: Re: RAM=HD to Rick Hodger

Hello Jamie

On 08-nov-98, Jamie Bentley wrote:
> You didn't understand me...
> 
> I meant that we shouldn't have HD's as such, but RAM chips (because their
> smaller) that do both ram AND HD  function, instant seek time, 2.1gb per
> second loading time, and you can simply unplug it and take it to a  friends
> house.

you mean static ram ? Unfortunately static RAM is much too expensive and far
more inefficient than normal RAM. The biggest PCMCIA static RAM commercially
available today is probably about 32 or 64 MB. That would have been alright
as a hard-drive 10 years ago, unfortunately a 4 GB hard-drive would be much
cheaper than a 64 MB SD-RAM. That's why hard-drives are so popular, because
they're cheap ie. you get a lot of storage for a small amount of money. I
beleive that a JAZ or a JAZ2 is a much better system as if you get
corruptions, you just use another cartridge, and the price for a cartridge is
very cheap as there's no mechanical parts, motors, PCB, etc. included in a
cartridge as with an actual hard-drive.

Regards
-- 
Stephen



@ENDNODE
