> second loading time, and you can simply unplug it and take it to a  friends
> house.

Hmmm.

So you can fit 50Gb of RAM in a 3.5" drive bay can you? 

It's all a case of price/performance. I have no desire to pay stupid 
amounts of money so that I can store gifs I rarely use in memory 
rather than on any form of backing store. Hey - why not use 
on-processor cache instead? Things would be even quicker then...

I can unplug a hard drive and take it to a friend's house. Your point?

