@NODE "Mail_449" "Re: RAM=HD to Rick Hodger"
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 06 Nov 1998 19:02:57 +0000
Organization: Corrupted Software
Subject: Re: RAM=HD to Rick Hodger

I watched as Jamie Bentley hammered "RAM=HD to Rick Hodger" out on
their keyboard...

JB> I meant that we shouldn't have HD's as such, but RAM chips
(because their
JB> smaller) that do both ram AND HD  function, instant seek time,
2.1gb per
JB> second loading time, and you can simply unplug it and take it to a
 friends
JB> house.

Gah!!! Still a daft idea! static memory is *very* expenisve and quite
unreliable.  They can be wiped be going near a weak magnetic field,
and a power surge can kill one.  Plus they can only be written to so
many times before that chunk becomes read-only, and if you're using
that for memory as well as storage....the entire system would be
unusable after a couple of weeks of heavy use.

-- 
