@NODE "Mail_473" "Re: Romulus the 2nd"
          (Post.Office MTA Undefined release Undefined
          ID# 0-52107U250000L250000S0V35) with SMTP id net
          for <blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie>; Sat, 21 Nov 1998 18:20:34 +0000
From: "Xyz Scott" <xyz.scott@virgin.net>
Subject: Re: Romulus the 2nd
Date: Sat, 21 Nov 1998 18:15:24 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-2"
Encoding: 7bit

On 21st-Nov-1998 M. Misic threw his hands in the air and uttered:

>Hmmm...this file i always have, and ever when i use commands from it
>witihn a blitz-code i got this error-message:

>                 Library not found   :   $0020

>Because of this i thought that this file was only a part of the
>*RomulusConsoleLibrary* and asked you to get the missing part.

>Now i see, these obj-File was the whole part of this library package, but
>why do i get this error-message ?
>I get it while compiling and running and by creating an executable, too.

>Any ideas ?

Hmmmm.  I cranked up Blitz, tapped in a few commands from the above
mentioned lib, hit compile and run, and hey presto:

                                  Library not found  :  $0020

Shows how often I use commands from this lib eh?   (;

Anyway, the error is because Blitz cannot find the numbered library that
the token refers to (ie $0020 or 32 for us humans)  For some reason, this
lib insists on being number 32, so to fix the problem, load up a hex editor,
and change the 38th byte (counting 1 as the first byte) and change it to $20
and then recompile your deflibs (if you still do)  It should cure the error
message problem.

Regards

Scott

xyz.scott@virgin.net




@ENDNODE
