From: "Xyz Scott" <xyz.scott@virgin.net>
Subject: Re: Romulus the 2nd
Date: Sun, 22 Nov 1998 13:21:05 -0000
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_0017_01BE161A.F5A2CAC0"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_0017_01BE161A.F5A2CAC0
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit

On 22nd-Nov-1998, M. Misic pressed some keys on his
keyboard and came up with this:

>> For some reason, this lib insists on being number 32,
>> so to fix the problem, load up a hex editor, and change the
>> 38th byte (counting 1 as the first byte) and change it to $20
>> and then recompile your deflibs (if you still do)  It should cure the
>> error message problem.

> Ehh...what exactly should i load into the editor ?

> The Lib or the Deflibs-file ?
> I did it seperately with both, but i always get the same error as before.
> :-(


First, make sure you don't have any other lib at number 32, and then
you need to edit the 'RomulusConsoleLib.obj' file.  To make sure you
edit the correct byte, in the attachment I sent before, byte 38 contains
$43, or 67 in decimal.  Change this byte to $20, or 32 in decimal.
Then you must remake your deflibs before running Blitz.
Actually, forget all that.  I'll just send the edited lib...   (;
Chuck this into your libs drawer and remake your deflibs.
Fingers crossed...

Regards

Scott

xyz.scott@virgin.net



