Hi Jake,

On 31-Oct-98, Jake Frederick wrote:
> On 31-Oct-98, Curt Esser wrote:
>> 
>> Here is an example.
> 
> Thanks, but how could I have the scroll controlled by joystick movement
rather
> than the mouse autoscrolling? I'm making a game that requires scrolling when
a
> shape reaches the edge of the bitmap. Also would this method allow the
> implementation of a non scrolling, lores score display on the top of the
> screen? 

OK, here is a way to do it.  You use 2 screens, one for the score display, and
one for the scrolling game screen.  Note that the 2 screens can be different
depths, have different palettes, and even could be different screen modes if
you want.

I have made them attached together, so they will always depth-arrainge as if
it was one screen.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


