@NODE "Mail_492" "Re: Screen Tags"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 13 Nov 1998 21:11:16 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Fri, 13 Nov 1998 20:37:47 +0000
Subject: Re: Screen Tags

Hi,

> Where can I get a list of the different screen tags? Specifically I need
> the dislpay number for a 640x480 productivity screen, but having them all
> would be usefull.

tags for width, height and ModeID are:-

#SA_Width, #SA_Height and #SA_DisplayID

The list in full is:-

#SA_Left
#SA_Top
#SA_Width
#SA_Height
#SA_Depth
#SA_DetailPen
#SA_BlockPen
#SA_Title
#SA_Colors
#SA_ErrorCode
#SA_Font
#SA_SysFont
#SA_Type
#SA_BitMap
#SA_PubName
#SA_PubSig
#SA_PubTask
#SA_DisplayID
#SA_DClip
#SA_Overscan
#SA_Obsolete1
#SA_ShowTitle
#SA_Behind
#SA_Quiet
#SA_AutoScroll
#SA_Pens
#SA_FullPalette
#SA_ColorMapEntries
#SA_Parent
#SA_Draggable
#SA_Exclusive
#SA_SharePens
#SA_BackFill
#SA_Interleaved
#SA_Colors32
#SA_VideoControl
#SA_FrontChild
#SA_BackChild
#SA_LikeWorkbench
#SA_Reserved
#SA_MinimizeISG

More info on these tags are found in the autodocs, or the include
files that come with various languages Asm, C or Blitz.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - burkey.home.ml.org >



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_493" "Re: Screen Tags"
          Paris Fri, 13 Nov 1998 21:07:44 +0100 (MET)
          Paris Fri, 13 Nov 1998 21:07:42 +0100 (MET)
From: Vincent Demongodin <v.demongodin@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Fri, 13 Nov 1998 21:04:19 -0500
Subject: Re: Screen Tags
Encoding: quoted-printable

Le 12-Nov-98, Jake Frederick a =E9crit:

>Where can I get a list of the different screen tags? Specifically I need=
 the
>dislpay number for a 640x480 productivity screen, but having them all wo=
uld
be
>usefull.
>-- =

>-If the doors of perception were cleansed everything would appear to man=
 as
it
>truly is, infinite.-

If you don't want to search for TAGS in C/ASM include, use this little pr=
og
to find Display ID:


NEWTYPE .screeninfo
  id.l       ;Display ID
  width.l
  height.l
  depth.w
  overscan.w
  autoscroll.w
  bmapwidth.l
  bmapheight.l
End NEWTYPE


*sc.screeninfo=3DASLScreenRequest(31)
If *sc
  NPrint "#SA_Display ID for this mode: ", *sc\id," =3D ",Hex$(*sc\id)
EndIf


End





-- =

Vincent Demongodin
v.demongodin@wanadoo.fr
Old A1200/68030 50Mhz - DD 540 Mo - 32 Mo RAM



