Subject: Screen Tags & Double Buffering

   I am writing a program that uses screen tags to scroll around on a bitmap
that's on a large screen. I am trying to use double  buffering to blit some
shapes
on top of the scrolling screen but have run into a slight problem. While
scrolling the shape jumps back and forth like it's shaking. I think the
problem is occuring because when I move the screen it's also moving the shapes
that are blitted to it making them are move ahead twice as much as they
normally
would and then jumping back to their normal position when they are blitted
again. Has anyone done what I'm trying to do? If so I would really appreciate
some help or examples.
-- 
