@NODE "Mail_503" "Re: Screens"
          with SMTP id <19981107142225.BCKN27884@ameritech.net>;
          Sat, 7 Nov 1998 08:22:25 -0600
From: pkocourek@ameritech.net (Paul Kocourek)
Date: Sat, 07 Nov 1998 08:27:11
Subject: Re: Screens
Organization: None (sh82)
X-Receipt: No
X-Form: Standard.FORM

> On Wed, 28 Oct 1998 12:21:53 +0000 you wrote:

> 
> Hello,
> 
> Does anyone know how to display a picture in hires-laced
at
> 640x512 with 256
> colours (8 bitplanes) on a normal window. I've tried this,
but
> I just get
> corrupt graphics on the screen, and when I try to quit
the programme,
> it
> says 'unable to free memory'. The biggest picture I've
managed
> to do in
> hires-laced with 8 bitplanes is 512x512. (The problems
happen
> if I try to
> make the width any bigger than 512.) 
> 
> Can someone please help me?
> 
> Here is bit of code from the programme that I have done.
> 
> Best Regards
> 
> Stuart Walker
> 
> Digital Images
> 
> e-mail:stuart@digital-images.demon.co.uk
> Website:http://www.digital-images.demon.co.uk
> 

Try the following changes:

WBStartup
NoCli
Screen 0,0,0,640,512,8,$C,"",1,0  ;use the long form of the
Screen command
LoadShape 0,"Space_Station_2:Station2/StationInt",0 ;this
is OK, but you need an explicit loadpalette cmd:
LoadPalette 0,"Space_Station_2:Station2/StationInt"
;drop this--it's for Blitz mode only   > InitCopList 0,44,256,$10008,0,256,0
; drop this > BitMap 0,640,512,8
Screensbitmap 0,0  ;this accesses the Bitmap created by the
Screen command
Use Screen 0
Showscreen 0
Window 0,0,0,640,512,$1800,"",0,0
ShowPalette 0
;drop this.  It's automatically taken care of by the Showscreen
cmd.   ShowBitMap 0
Blit 0,0,0
BitMaptoWindow 0,0
MouseWait
Free Palette 0
closewindow 0  ;use this instead of Free BitMap 0 ;By the
way, you MUST close the Window FIRST, then the Screen
closescreen 0; use this instead of> Free Window 0
End
> 
> 
ç

--



