Hi there,

I am developing KRUD TV, an OS friendly TV station management sim in Blitz.
The problem is that shunting windows around the display of my game is very
slow. I know the source of the problem, though. I have a picture in the
background so that there isn't too much grey on the screen. The way I do
this is to have a background window containing the picture. Even though the
depth of the screen is only 6 bitplanes, moving windows is far to slow. Any
suggestions?

Nick



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_519" "Re: Slloooowww"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Wed, 25 Nov 1998 21:56:37 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
