Subject: Re: Slloooowww

Hi,

> I am developing KRUD TV, an OS friendly TV station management sim in
Blitz.
> The problem is that shunting windows around the display of my game is very
> slow. <..............................> Even though the depth of the screen
is only 6
> bitplanes, moving windows is far to slow. Any suggestions?

Tell us more about what you mean by 'shunting windows'... On an
intuition screen you should be able to move a Window from one
place to another in an instant. The way Windows and more importantly
RastPorts and Layers work in connection with Amigas hardware
there's no actual data being moved anywhere. Maybe I've just been
using super fast gfx-card displays for too long but it seems you're
doing something strange. Perhaps I just don't understand what you're
really doing.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

