I sold Nick Berry a hi-fi the other day, by the way. Anyway, it is just a
plain ordinary case of dragging a window. This is being done under AGA, not
a graphics card. I have an unmoveable window containing a picture in the
background, and other windows that can move freely on top of this. The
problem is how slowly they redraw at their new location once moved. If I
lose the background window, everything happens (as you say) instantly. The
problem is that Intuition obviously has to redraw the background window
everytime I move one of the other windows, making the process take about 1.5
seconds (a real pain). I guess what I am really asking is if I can display a
picture behind my windows without using a background window. Sorry if this
is getting complicated. Thanks.

Nick / Skillo



