> lose the background window, everything happens (as you say) instantly. The
> problem is that Intuition obviously has to redraw the background window
> everytime I move one of the other windows, making the process take about
> 1.5 seconds (a real pain). I guess what I am really asking is if I can
> display a picture behind my windows without using a background window.

Okay, well this is probably what i dreaded... It's normal! :) I really
should try
using AGA once in a while to appreciate how nice gfx-cards are!

Most of this advice is based around WB screens but may also help with
your own screens and windows...

You could try using a different version of IPrefs like for example
'FastIPrefs'
which is on Aminet. This does a few fancy things that can save memory and
could also speed up your system. There may also be other speedup methods
such as using 'FBlit' (fast ram cpu version of OS blitting functions) and
also
try out an alternative WBPattern prefs app (I think this comes with
FastIPrefs)
which lets you setup various precision options. There has to be a limit the
performance of an AGA based display update but perhaps you can make
things go that little bit faster with a few tweaks. 

Cheers,

-- 
