@NODE "Mail_523" "Re: Slloooowww"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 26 Nov 1998 18:29:26 -0500
Subject: Re: Slloooowww

Hi Niels

On 26-Nov-98, Niels Chapman wrote:

>> Hi,
>> 
>>> I am developing KRUD TV, an OS friendly TV station management sim in
>> Blitz.
>>> The problem is that shunting windows around the display of my game is
> very
>>> slow. <..............................> Even though the depth of the
> screen
>> is only 6
>>> bitplanes, moving windows is far to slow. Any suggestions?
>> 
>> Tell us more about what you mean by 'shunting windows'...
> 
> All I mean is clicking on the window's title bar and dragging it to a new
> location.
> Anyway, it is just a
> plain ordinary case of dragging a window. This is being done under AGA,
not
> a graphics card. I have an unmoveable window containing a picture in the
> background, and other windows that can move freely on top of this. The
> problem is how slowly they redraw at their new location once moved. If I
> lose the background window, everything happens (as you say) instantly.
The
> problem is that Intuition obviously has to redraw the background window
> everytime I move one of the other windows, making the process take about
> 1.5 seconds (a real pain). I guess what I am really asking is if I can
> display a picture behind my windows without using a background window.
> Sorry if this is getting complicated. Thanks.

You can display a picture directly on the screen's bitmap without the
background window.  But I don't think it would help much, as intuition
would still have to redraw the parts that had been covered by the window
when you move it. And this wouldn't work on GFX cards (as I understand it)

Also, the more windows you have open on the screen, the slower the redraw
will be.

The only real solution is a faster processor and/or a GFX card.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




