@NODE "Mail_530" "RE: solid mode"
From: "C.J.R.Jarvis" <C.J.R.Jarvis@wkac.ac.uk>
Subject: RE: solid mode
Date: Tue, 24 Nov 1998 13:52:00 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Solidmode basically blits all areas os=f you shape that are not colour 0
(i.e. like a matte paint mode) as solid colour. For some reason however, it
always uses the colour at the top of your palette. i.e. in 8bits it uses
colour 255 and in 5 bits it uses colour 31.
	Does anyone know how you can set the colour of the Solidmode?

Chris Jarvis
