@NODE "Mail_532" "Re: solid mode"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Nov 1998 15:21:15 -0500
Subject: Re: solid mode

Hi Paul

On 23-Nov-98, Paul wrote:
> Hi.
> 
> Has anyone used the blitmode (qblitmode, sblitmode etc) called
> SolidMode?
> 
> Does it render the cookie as solid or does it do a `replace' (ie
> ignore the mask)?

Solidmode blits all the non 0 colours as one colour.

If you want to blit the whole shape including colour 0, use $DCA.
This blits the whole rectangle as-is, ignoring the cookie.


