@NODE "Mail_542" "Re: sound samples"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Tue, 17 Nov 1998 19:26:03 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Nov 1998 20:12:10 +0000
Subject: Re: sound samples

Hi,

> Slight dilema....maybe someone here knows?
> How exactly do you find the length of a sample already loaded into
> memory? I've tried using the .sound type with the \_length bit.....but
> if I load a sample of around 150k, it reports it as being a mere 23k. 

I use the following structure:

NEWTYPE .mysound
  _data.l
  _period.w
  _length.l
  _loop.l
  _looplength.w
End NEWTYPE

Using his structure you should be able to get the real sound length
using the following code:

LoadSound 0,"mysample"
*snd.mysound=Addr Sound(0)
length=*snd\_length*2

It should give you an accurate length for your 150k sample although
I'm not so confident that Blitz will play samples that long. I thought
128k was the maximum length for the 'Sound' command.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - http://www.sneech.demon.co.uk >

