From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 17 Nov 1998 21:18:43 +0000
Subject: Re: sound samples

Rick Hodger churned out *this* drivel :

> How exactly do you find the length of a sample already loaded into
> memory? I've tried using the .sound type with the \_length bit.....but
> if I load a sample of around 150k, it reports it as being a mere 23k. 

If I remember rightly, the OS as standard only allows samples
up to 128k (0-127). Because your sample's 150k, you get 150-127 (unsigned
bytes
or something) which = 23k...

I think you've got to do things your own way if you want more than 128k...
though I may be wrong...

I am, aren't I? :)

See ya,
-- 
James L Boyd - Team *AMIGA*
