--BOUNDARY.1748200480.2

Hi Dave,

On 29-Nov-98, Dave wrote:
> Hi,
> 
>     Anyone know how to program the sound of an engine?
>     I want the sound to change with different revs like in
>     skidmark.

I have attached a little example.  It uses the included sound sample (a
helicopter), but it will work (with adjustments) with any looping iff
sample.

>     Also I was wondering if anyone has any advice for how
>     to play Music , engine sounds for more than one car and
>     SoundFx like skiding, only using 4 channels?  I do have
>     the Music only using one channel atm.

Hmmm, sounds like a car-racing game  -  boy, am I perceptive, or what?  ;)

If you are going to use looping (continous) engine sounds, like in the
example, and the standard Amiga hardware (4 channels), you will need a
separate channel for each car, I'm afraid.  You can over-ride the engine
sound with the skidding, etc, when necessary.  You might also get by with
using only two car sound channels - the player's and a "generic"
all-other-cars channel, if you are having a 1 player vs the computer cars
game, and then use the other two channels for the module. 

<sb>

Later...

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748200480.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="engine.examp.asc"

LoadSound 0,"Heli.iff"    ;this sound must have it's loop set!
                          ;you can do this in your sample editor
                          ;Octamed has a nice sample editor, BTW,
                          ;and it's now freeware!

LoopSound 0,15            ;start it continous-playing


lowest.w=Peek.w(Addr Sound (0)+4)   ;the default period
highest.w=lowest-170                ;adjust this to get the correct value
                                    ;for your own sound sample
                                    ;note that lower values give a higher
                                    ;pitch to the sample
pitch.w=lowest


Repeat                              ;your main program loop

VWait

dir.b= Joyy(1)                      ;joystick up/down
If dir                              ;up=faster (higher pitch)
                                    ;down=slower (lower pitch)
  pitch.w+dir
  If pitch<highest Then pitch=highest
  If pitch > lowest Then pitch=lowest
  Freq 15,pitch
EndIf

If Joyb(1)                          ;joystick button was pressed

  Repeat                            ;slow down if needed (land the heli!)
    pitch+1
    Freq 15,pitch
    VWait
  Until pitch=>lowest

  VWait 100                         ;pause a bit
  vol.b=64                          ;fade out the volume
  Repeat
    VWait 3
    Volume 15,vol,vol,vol,vol
    vol-1
  Until vol=0
  Quiet 15                          ;stop all sounds
  End
EndIf


Forever

--BOUNDARY.1748200480.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="sound.lha"
