@NODE "Mail_559" "Re: Stonecracker Code"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 29 Nov 1998 17:08:15 +0000
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@velvety.demon.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 29 Nov 1998 17:04:50 +0000
Subject: Re: Stonecracker Code

sweeney stephen j churned out *this* drivel :

> Where can I find examples of how to use this? I've seen people talking
> about it, but I can't find any example code.

Stonecracker is a file packer, just like PowerPacker.

The difference is that :
 
a) it makes slightly smaller files,
                       
b) runs on *any* Amiga (well, 1.3+ I think)
                       
c) you have a choice of making it use built-in code in your executable
   or, to squeeze a few more bytes out of it, you can make it use its own
   stc.library. The first option is best as it means your users don't even
   need stc.library.

I've never had any problems with it, and tried it under OS2.0 -> 3.1...

I think it might be under "stc" on Aminet (if you can't find it, I'll mail
it).

Oh, and it's totally free :)

Makes your program use about a third less disk space! I use it on
everything
I do now...

See ya,
-- 
James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
Team *AMIGA*, member of *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
Connected from Dundee, Scotland...




