@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_571" "RE: System Friendly Fading"
From: "C.J.R.Jarvis" <C.J.R.Jarvis@wkac.ac.uk>
Subject: RE: System Friendly Fading
Date: Wed, 18 Nov 1998 10:59:02 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-1"

Statement fadeo{r,g,b}
   r=AGARed(0)
   g=AGAGreen(0)
   b=AGAblue(0)
   While b>0 or g>0 or b>0
      If r>0 then r-1
      If g>0 then g-1
      if b>0 then b-1
      AGARGB 0,r,g,b
   Wend
End Statement
      
This won't work properly, as it fades all the  parts of the palette at the
same rate, so for instance a colour with contains R=100 G=255 B=0 will lose
all its red first, and the colour will turn green. Instead use a second
palette object and use this:

Initpalette 1,256
for n=0 to 1 step .005 (change this value for different spped fades)
	copypalette 0,1
	fadepalette 1,n
	vwait
	use palette 1
next n

err that should work. I use it in Timecampaign, and I'm fairly sure that's
the routine I use, although I don't have the source with me.

	Chris Jarvis


