@NODE "Mail_582" "Re: Text On A Bitmap"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    30 Nov 98 10:22:29 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 30 Nov 1998 10:22:11 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Text On A Bitmap

On 28 Nov 98, at 2:09, Stuart Walker wrote:

> If I load in a picture and then blit it on a window, bitmap etc.and then
> use the Print or the NPrint command, the text leaves a black border arou=
nd
> itself. Is there any way to stop that black border from appearing or is
> there an alternative command? I would just like to render the text to th=
e
> display without the black borders going over the picture. 

Here's a little routine I wrote, NOTE THAT IT DOESNT WORK and 
CRASHES. You've been warned, now its your fault if your house burns 
down. I don't know why but its probably something small. WinUAE has 
been p*ssing me off today. The principle should work though: create a 
rastport and write the text through that using OS functions (probably 
haven't set up the rastport properly or something, grumble, 
grumble....)

; Load font you want to print
LoadFont 0,"topaz.font",8

; The bitmap we are going to draw ovber the top of
BitMap 0,640,256,3
For i.w=3D0 To 200
  Line Rnd(640),Rnd(256),Rnd(640),Rnd(256),Rnd(8)
Next

; Statement to print foreground only (with newline)
Statement NFGPrint{text.s}
  DEFTYPE._RastPort rp	; RastPort

  ; Initialise ratport, set up bitmap pointer, font, foreground
  ; colour and drawing mode
  InitRastPort_ &rp
  rp\_BitMap =3D Addr BitMap(0)
  SetFont_ &rp,Peek.l(Addr IntuiFont(0))
  SetDrMd_ &rp,#JAM1
  SetAPen_ &rp,#TEXTPEN

  ; Add a newline, this is like NPrint
  text=3Dtext+Chr$(10)
  Text_ &rp,text,Len(text)
End Statement

; Print some text
NFGPrint{""}
NFGPrint{""}
NFGPrint{"           Bite me"}

; Show results on a screen.
Screen 0,0,0,640,256,3,$8000,"e",0,1,0

ClickMouse
End


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694
  http://members.xoom.xom/David_McMinn


