@NODE "Mail_584" "Re: Text Width"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    23 Nov 98 11:03:50 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 1998 11:03:32 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: Text Width

On 23 Nov 98, at 10:49, S9225796 asked a question which has been 
answered more times than "So, you saw Elvis in your local 
laundrette?";)

> I was just wondering how to figure out the width of a text string which
> uses a variable character width, such as personal.font. usually when i d=
o:
> 
>      w=3Dlen(string$)*8
> 
> it works fine for 8x8 fonts, but I do I do it for non 8x8 fonts?


 (You'll need amigalibs.res for this)

DEFTYPE.RastPort rp
InitRastPort_ &rp
LoadFont 0,"personal.font",8
SetFont_ &rp, Peek.l(Addr IntuiFont(0))
w.w =3D TextLength_(&rp,&string$,Len(string$))

 If you already have your font loaded and are using it to print in a 
window, you can use:

LoadFont 0,"personal.font",8
WindowFont 0
w.w =3D TextLength_(RastPort(0),&string$,Len(string$))


