@NODE "Mail_590" "This is a Blitz list"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 6 Nov 1998 23:01:13 +0000
From: "Nick Chapman" <scillo@geocities.com>
Subject: This is a Blitz list
Date: Fri, 6 Nov 1998 22:48:15 -0000
	boundary="----=_NextPart_000_015D_01BE09D7.8A3C9F80"

This is a multi-part message in MIME format.

------=_NextPart_000_015D_01BE09D7.8A3C9F80
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: quoted-printable

Hello everyone.

Sorry that I have mailed so many things to the list at once. I have a =
lot to say, obviously! I have 2 things to say. Firstly, the manual is =
going very well. I have stumbled across a couple of areas that I am not =
expert in, however, so I will shortly be calling on you guys for a bit =
of help.

Secondly, this is a Blitz list. Please: take the non-Blitz conversation =
threads to other mailing lists or even newsgroups. They will be =
appreciated there and you will receive far more responses. It is =
irritating for those of us who are looking for an answer to a question =
we have posted or trying to help someone out if there are loads of other =
messages in the way. This has only happened to a great extent this week, =
so let's hope it was just a freak happening. I mean...for some guy to be =
slating BASIC while bored round a mate's house, and another conversation =
discussing the relative merits of different removable media forms...take =
it elsewhere! They are valid topics, especially the ones about the =
Amiga's future. But as far as this list goes, it is BY Blitz users FOR =
Blitz users. Nuff said.

Oh, this might sound hypocritical after what I just said, but I am =
telling everyone. Paul Capewell, one of Skillo's chief programmers (and =
in charge of Martian Tales, coded in Blitz) recently bought an SVGA =
monitor and internal scan-doubler for his A1200. After a few days of =
brilliant use, the scan-doubler cooked the inside of his A1200, =
including the AGA chipset and his Hard Drive. As such, Martian Tales is =
now no longer going to happen. Months of hard work have been wasted, and =
the future of Skillo is looking doubtful. BE CAREFUL.

Nick / Skillo

------=_NextPart_000_015D_01BE09D7.8A3C9F80
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: quoted-printable

