@NODE "Mail_598" "Tokenising"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    2 Nov 98 09:06:38 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 2 Nov 1998 09:06:30 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Tokenising

 I've only just noticed this since I've got my 060, but when I'm 
typing something in Blitz, it tries to tokenise it after every 
character. For example, if I type 'population' the 'Pop' part gets 
tokenised, but once I type the next character, it returns to normal. 
However, this is annoying, as I end up with Population instead of 
Population. No problem I hear you cry, just use Population 
everywhere. Well your right, but its sooooooo annoying, as I normally 
use lower case names for variables, no capitals or underscores at the 
start, although I'll probably have to now.


