@NODE "Mail_613" "Re: WBStartup bug detection..."
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Mon, 9 Nov 1998 00:53:34 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Mon, 09 Nov 1998 01:26:06 +0000
Subject: Re: WBStartup bug detection...

Hi,

> Hi Paul, James,
> You've asked to know how detect the WBStartup bug. I've build quickly a
> small package which contain all necessary stuffs.

The test.exe file you provided (744 bytes) that does indeed cause a
guru when run using your WBStart.exe test program. You included
the source code which consisted of the simple 'WBStartup:End'... I
compiled this myself but my own version of Blitz compiled the test.exe
to 1,360 bytes. The version I compiled didn't cause a guru when
I tested it with your WBStartup.exe program. So, maybe you have
an old version of acidlibs or something.

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - burkey.home.ml.org >



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_614" "Re: WBStartup bug detection..."
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Mon, 09 Nov 1998 04:54:12 -0500
Subject: Re: WBStartup bug detection...

Hi,

On 08-Nov-98, Paul Burkey wrote:
> Hi,
> 
>> Hi Paul, James,
>> You've asked to know how detect the WBStartup bug. I've build quickly a
>> small package which contain all necessary stuffs.
> 
> The test.exe file you provided (744 bytes) that does indeed cause a
> guru when run using your WBStart.exe test program. You included
> the source code which consisted of the simple 'WBStartup:End'... I
> compiled this myself but my own version of Blitz compiled the test.exe
> to 1,360 bytes. The version I compiled didn't cause a guru when
> I tested it with your WBStartup.exe program. So, maybe you have
> an old version of acidlibs or something.

I had a little different results with your test codes.  I have the same
version of wbstart.library as the one you sent, and WB 3.1

1. Text.exe (the bugged one you sent) Ran WBStart.exe by clicking it's icon -
no crashes.  I did this 20 times.  I even rebooted my system myself and tried
this again to be sure.

2. Fixed exe also ran no problems.

3. I did as Paul, and compiled my own "test.exe".  I also get file size 1360
bytes.
This too ran with no problems.

4. I tried renaming several full Blitz programs, by myself & others, as
"test.exe" and ran these with WBstart.exe.  Again, no problems, all worked
correctly.

My two cents: Although you both must have different Acidlibs (the file size
difference) I don't think that is the problem.  I would check your C:SetPatch
command (I have version 43.7) to make sure it is up to date.  I once had a
problem when some program installed a different (older) setpatch command on my
system.  This made several other programs (most NOT Blitz programs) crash and
do other strange things.  It's just a hunch, but worth checking.


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
