@NODE "Mail_616" "WBStartup really bugged !"
From: =?iso-8859-1?Q?Fr=E9d=E9ric?= Laboureur <alphasnd@sdv.fr>
Date: Sun, 08 Nov 1998 10:12:26 +0100
Organization: Fantaisie Software
Subject: WBStartup really bugged !
Encoding: quoted-printable


    Hi Blitzers,

    Just a little mail to inform you that the WBStartup command is bugged=

and could cause many crash to your program. I've discovered it when I've
written TheBoss (a program launcher) and would launch my Blitz2 program i=
n
the WB way (using the wbstart.library). All crashed. First I've think tha=
t
was a bug in the wbstart.library :-). Finally, after writting the NWbStar=
tup
for the NCS, and used it at each time (for testing reasons ? :-). The
proggies runs well with TheBoss. This bug is present in the ScalOS too, w=
hen
launchin a Blitz proggy from floppy disk (don't ask me why) in the WB way=
=2E

    You should forget 'NumPar' and 'Par$' commands which cause exactly th=
e
same crash (ie: if you remove the old WBStartup and keep these commands,
there is no effect).

    I think this is very important bug, so please to avoid it. You have 2=

ways to remove this bug:

    + Use your own WBStart routine (easy to do, but be sure to reply the
WBMessage at the end :-)
    + Use the NWBStartup routine, which is in the WbStartup.obj of the NC=
S
V1.40.
It works perfectly too. Just install only this lib if you don't want all =
the
others :-).

    Thanks for reading this, your programs/games depends of it.

        Regards,

                        Fred.

<sb>

        /\/\/\/\/\                    Fr=E9d=E9ric Laboureur (Fred)
     __/          \_    =

    /^ ^  u^ ^n  ^ ^\               E-Mail Address: alphasnd@sdv.fr =

   (o o_ /(o o)\ _o o)  =

