@NODE "Mail_617" "Re: WBStartup really bugged !"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Sun, 8 Nov 1998 15:35:15 +0000
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 08 Nov 1998 15:53:19 +0000
Subject: Re: WBStartup really bugged !

Hi,

>    Just a little mail to inform you that the WBStartup command is bugged
> and could cause many crash to your program. I've discovered it when I've
> written TheBoss (a program launcher) and would launch my Blitz2 program in
> the WB way (using the wbstart.library). All crashed. First I've think that
> was a bug in the wbstart.library :-). Finally, after writting the
> NWbStartup for the NCS, and used it at each time (for testing reasons ?

It seems odd that WBStatup has been used in virtually every Blitz
release ever. Also odd to discover that one of my own games
that is used by many thousands of people also uses this command
and should be causing problems to many users. Despite this I've
never recieved any bug reports that would point to this kind of
problem. Can you tell me how I could test this bug out for myself?
If I'm going to change such an important part of my game, I need
to feel very sure that this is necessary before I risk opening up
to new bug reports. 

Cheers,

-- 
< Paul Burkey - burkey.home.ml.org >



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_618" "Re: WBStartup really bugged !"
 (envelope-from D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk)
    9 Nov 98 08:51:37 0
From: "David Mcminn" <D.McMinn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 9 Nov 1998 08:51:17 -0000
encoding: Quoted-printable
Subject: Re: WBStartup really bugged !

On 8 Nov 98, at 10:12, Fr=E9d=E9ric Laboureur wrote:
>     I think this is very important bug, so please to avoid it. You have =
2
> ways to remove this bug:
> 
>     + Use your own WBStart routine (easy to do, but be sure to reply the
> WBMessage at the end :-)

 Have you ever tried this in Blitz? Its doesn't like this in the 
slightest. If you run more than 1 copy of your program you *MUST* 
quit them in the opposite order from what they were started, 
otherwise all of the remaining ones hang and look like they go into 
busy waiting loops (very jerky response from mouse).

 I have plenty of code for doing this, but I've never got it working 
due to the above problem. I think the problem with doing this with 
Blitz is that it opens up libraries etc before your code, so all 
libraries are open before you do your WBStartup stuff. At the end, 
you have to free all libraries (except exec) before doing the Reply, 
and you can't do this in Blitz. Unless I'm wrong, in which case, 
someone send a working example to the list.


|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| =A9 |\/| ][ |\| |\|
  d.mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk ICQ=3D16827694


@ENDNODE
